title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sweet potatoes until smooth.
Add egg, sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together. Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Wash lemons; cut into thin strips and remove seeds.
Place lemon slices in a large bowl.
Cover with sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then press with a potato masher to get as much juice as you can from the lemons.
Add cold water and continue to press lemons with masher until liquid is well flavored.
Pour over 2 ice cubes in a tall glass.
Add a lemon slice to each glass.

title: sherry tea cakes
directions: Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Bake in small muffin pans.

title: german potato salad(microwave)
directions: Chop bacon.
Peel and cut
potatoes into 1/4-inch slices. Place bacon and green onion in small bowl.
Cover and microwave on High until bacon is light brown, about 7 minutes.
Stir in vinegar, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Place potato slices and water in 2-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High until potatoes are fork-tender.
Pour bacon and vinegar mixture over potatoes.
Toss to coat.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together butter and sugars; beat with mixer until smooth. Add eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Roll dough into a ball and refrigerate overnight or until thoroughly chilled.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Cook butter and sugar over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue to cook until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool and add confectioners sugar.
Makes a lot of icing.

title: swiss n chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients except walnuts. Spoon into 2 quart casserole; sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion until meat is brown.
Stir until meat crumbles; drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes; stir often.

title: shrimp salad a la finland
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size chunks.
Add all other ingredients and toss well.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with buttermilk dressing.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thick strips; coat with flour, salt and pepper.
Fry until golden brown.
Combine onion soup mix, dressing and pineapple preserves in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until well mixed.
Pour over chicken.
Serve with rice and steamed vegetables.

title: english muffin goodies
directions: Mix ingredients (except muffins or bread) thoroughly. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Spread over muffins or bread slices that have been quartered.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and bread toasts.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes; cook in boiling salted water until tender. Remove from water and cool.
Peel and grate with a coarse grater. Add sour cream, onions, cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix and turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: my favorite tea cakes(sugar cinnamon cookies or snickerdoodles)
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add egg, salt, vanilla, baking soda and cinnamon and mix well.
Add flour and mix thoroughly. Wrap dough in plastic wrap and chill at least 1 hour.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: In your food processor, grate 1 carrot.
Flip blade and slice cabbage; mix well.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute celery, bell pepper and onion until just tender.
Mix with cooked rice and other ingredients.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate nut bark
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler; add nuts.
Pour onto wax paper or small greased cookie sheet.
Cool completely and break up.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Let sit 4 to 5 hours.

title: chicken wings - buffalo style
directions: *For hotter wings, use up to 3/4 cup (6 ounces).

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Melt butter; add celery and onion.
Cook over medium-low heat until tender.
Stir in croutons, cornbread and pecans and seasonings.
Add eggs and toss lightly.
Pour hot broth and cream of chicken soup over entire mixture; toss.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 14 cups.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine milk, water, vinegar and molasses. Stir into dry ingredients.
Add melted shortening and stir until smooth. Pour into greased 9-inch layer cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cut corn close to outer edge, cutting twice around ear.
Scrape ear to remove all the milk.
Have skillet warm; add drippings and corn.
(Add water if too dry.)
Stir constantly for a minute and add milk, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes or until thickened.
Watch and stir often.
Add butter the last few minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine lettuce, peas, onion and cheese in medium bowl. Chill.
Toss with dressing before serving.

title: whiskey sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Boil potatoes (peeled and chunked); then mash.
Add all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered dish; bake for 30 minutes.
Five minutes before finished, add small marshmallows on top.

title: carolyn's chicken enchiladas
directions: For Sauce: Melt butter in a saucepan. Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add broth. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in coriander and half the chilies. In a bowl, combine chicken, Monterey Jack cheese and remaining chilies. Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture onto each tortilla. Roll up and place seam side down in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour sauce over enchiladas. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted. Yields 4 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, milk and cooking oil.
Mix until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture, then add vanilla and poppy seed.
Pour batter in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.

title: chicken and brie
directions: Saute garlic, onion and mushrooms.
Set aside.
Saute chicken breast.
Add veggies and cheese until cheese is melted.
Add to pasta and serve.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: In a large cast-iron skillet, cook meat, drain and sprinkle with 1/2 package of spaghetti sauce mix.
Spoon cottage cheese over meat.
Top with noodles in a layer and sprinkle with remaining sauce mix, basil and parsley.
Pour tomatoes, tomato sauce and 8 ounces of water over top.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 35 minutes until noodles are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese, cover and let stand 5 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Crush cranberries and add sugar.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Drain cranberries of juice.
Add 2 cups of red seedless grapes, cut in two, and chopped nuts; mix well.
Fold in whipping cream (whipped).
Chill until ready to serve.

title: judy's doughnuts
directions: Beat flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg until light.
Add eggs, sugar, butter and sour milk; go light on the flour.
Fry in hot Crisco oil.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: crab puffs
directions: Spread with spoon on muffin quarters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Freeze at least 30 minutes.
Remove from freezer and place under broiler until they are slightly golden brown and puff up (about 5 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Trim crust edges off bread.
Grate cucumber; drain well on paper towel.
Mix softened cream cheese with garlic salt and grated onion according to taste.
Blend in cucumber.
Spread very light coat of mayo on bread slices for easy spreading.
Spread mixture thinly on bread.
Cut sandwiches in fourths or halves.
Refrigerate until served.
(Good for parties.)

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Dot with butter and set aside. Combine 1 cup flour and salt; cut in shortening with a pastry cutter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle ice water one tablespoon at a time evenly over surface.
Stir with a fork until moistened.
Shape into a ball.

title: chicken devine
directions: Combine all these ingredients and cook on medium.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp and mushroom stuffing
directions: Slice mushrooms and chop shrimp.
Saute mushrooms in the 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp just turns color.
Add a little garlic salt.
Mix stuffing according to package directions but omit margarine.
Add shrimp/mushroom mixture to stuffing mix.
Microwave for 5 minutes.

title: lo-cal chocolate pudding
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar replacement, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat and cook 4 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount into egg, then pour back into cocoa mixture.
Stir to blend and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and oleo; cool.

title: layered jello dessert
directions: Crumble all ingredients together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sour cream biscuit
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into miniature muffin tins. Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: quick microwave chicken casserole
directions: Layer noodles, then soup, cheese and chicken.
Cook on High in microwave for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: diet dip
directions: Whip
cottage
cheese with a blender until smooth.
Add the sweetener
to taste.
Mix in the lemon juice.
Serve with the fresh fruit.

title: easy stew casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in oiled casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Can add vegetables last hour.
Easy!

title: blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges with juice; beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or layer 9-inch cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake according to package directions.
Cool on rack.
When cake is completely cooled frost with Cool Whip, pineapple and vanilla pudding.
Mix together pudding and pineapple for 3 minutes.
Add Cool Whip.
Let set 5 minutes.
Spread on cake.

title: hot sauce fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Put in
a large bowl.
Pour entire bottle of Texas Pete over chicken.
Mix well so that all parts are covered.
Let stand 1 hour. Take marinated chicken out of bowl. Dip in flour until covered.
Place in frying pan of corn oil at medium heat for approximately 20 minutes or until done. Serves 4.

title: bendel's baked wild rice
directions: Saute rice, onion and mushrooms in butter for 10 minutes.
Add broth and turn into a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix ingredients well and chill.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cool and drain linguine.
Chop vegetables very fine.
Add to linguine.
Toss with Seven Seas dressing and Salad Supreme.
Serve cold.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in 1/2 lengthwise and place peeled or unpeeled in microwave dish. Add water and cover. Microwave 10 minutes on High.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Put beef, onion, bell pepper and celery in a Dutch oven and steam covered
over
medium
heat
until meat turns white, breaking up meat with
a
fork as you stir occasionally.
Meat may be mashed fine
or	left
in bite size chunks, as desired. Add tomatoes, beans, salt
and	pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add cabbage, pushing it
under	liquid.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Adjust seasonings to your own taste.
You can put in a can of Ro-Tel if you like your food spicy.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Fill cups 1/3 full.
Top with 1 heaping teaspoonful of the filling mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Needs no frosting, and they taste great.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with Doritos. Combine remaining ingredients and layer over Doritos. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and cut into bite size pieces.
Boil rice in chicken stock until done.
Add Cheez Whiz, broccoli, soup and mushrooms to hot rice.
Stir all together and season to taste. Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and heat in 350° oven until cheese bubbles.

title: wine punch
directions: Mix sugar, wine and soda.
Slice unpeeled fruit and place in liquid.
Chill at least 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: red-cooked chicken
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, combine water, soy sauce, green onions, dry sherry, brown sugar, garlic and aniseed; mix well.
Place chicken in mixture, cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; let simmer for 25 minutes, using tongs to turn chicken over.
Cover again and let simmer for another 25 to 30 minutes more, basting frequently during the last 10 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets about 1 hour in a big pan.
Cold dip until skins come off.
Cut as desired and put in pan.
Cover beets with mixture.
Cook 15 minutes.
Put in jars while hot.

title: ms. v's white chili
directions: Cook turkey and onions until done.
Add spices.
Add broth, beans and chilies.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve topped with grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Serves about 6 people.

title: crock-pot macaroni pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a crock-pot which has been greased with 2 tablespoons of shortening (or spray with Pam). Cut several thin slices of cheese and put on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: best barbecue sauce(makes 4 cups)
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Note:
May be frozen.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet.
When bacon is half done, add onion, pepper and garlic; brown together.
Add rice, mushrooms, broth and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add more water if needed.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes, until rice is done.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Sift together salt, flour, soda and cinnamon. Stir into egg mixture and mix well. Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream cheese and oleo.
Add flour, sauce and Krispies.
Shape in marble-size balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Keep in tightly closed container in refrigerator.
Serve at room temperature.
May be frozen.

title: sausage and cheese bake
directions: Separate dough into 2 large rectangles.
Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Sprinkle sausage, then cheese over crust.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil whole can Eagle Brand milk (unopened; remove label) in water on top of stove for 3 hours. Open can and pour into crust. Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: super meat patties
directions: Mix all together. Shape into large patties, 2 to 2 1/2-inches in diameter and about 3/4 to 1-inch thick, by dropping heaping tablespoonful into handful of flour and shaping with another handful of flour. Brown fairly quickly in hot oil and set aside in baking pan. When all are brown, finish in oven for about 30 to 40 minutes. Pour off all but about 2 to 3 tablespoons of oil and make water gravy.

title: sauteed chicken pieces
directions: Saute the chicken pieces in margarine until browned.
Sprinkle on seasoned salt.
Place in Pyrex dish.
Pour wine over chicken; sprinkle thyme over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple on bottom of pan, then pour cherry pie filling on next.
Sprinkle cake mix over the fruit.
Pour melted butter over the top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: About 15 minutes before serving, cut top of broccoli into small flowerets; slice stalks into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Thinly slice carrots and green onions.
In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, in 1-inch boiling water, heat broccoli to boiling.
Cook, uncovered, 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut; allow to soak while preparing crust (15 minutes).
Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla and coconut mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until center is set.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic and onion.
Cook macaroni. Place Ricotta cheese in a medium mixing bowl; add egg and parsley and mix.
When other ingredients are cooked, get a large casserole dish and dump everything in it and mix.
Add Mozzarella cheese and mix again.
Sprinkle top with a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Make graham cracker crust.
Heat the marshmallows in the milk. Cool.
Add the chocolate and fold in the Cool Whip.
Put in crust.
Freeze.
Also good if you add nuts or top with dab of Cool Whip.
Put cherries on top. Sprinkle with nuts or chocolate shots for decoration.

title: fruit juice special
directions: Dissolve instant breakfast drink in water.
Add fruit juice, stirring to blend.
Serve in tall glasses with ice cubes.
Makes 3 1/3 cups or 3 servings.
Just mix and shake; perfect as breakfast drink, tall refresher or appetizer.

title: pork chop hongroise(serves 6)
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper and saute in butter in skillet.
Add onion, garlic, thyme and bay leaf and saute over medium-high heat until chops are well-browned.
Lower the heat and add chicken stock or wine. Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Remove chops to a warm serving platter and keep warm.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes, draining off excess water. Add egg and cracker meal. Mix well. Heat well-greased pan. Drop mixture by spoonfuls. Spread evenly and fry both sides until golden brown.

title: cherry walnut bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, lemon peel and undissolved yeast.
Combine milk, water and butter in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm. Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover with plastic wrap and towel; set aside for 20 minutes.
Combine walnuts, cherries and 3 tablespoons sugar.

title: chicken breast with curried vegetables
directions: In large, heavy skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add chicken; saute until light brown on both sides.
While browning chicken, stir curry powder and garlic into butter.
Add vermouth, salt and prunes.
Cover; simmer over low heat 5 to 7 minutes.
To test doneness, press finger into thickest part of chicken breast. Meat should spring back.
Place chicken on a plate and cover with skillet lid to keep warm.
Add vegetables to pan juices; stir. Cook until tender-crisp.
Place chicken on platter or individual plates.
Spoon vegetables and juices over.
Calories 242, fat 7.5 gm and fiber 2.3 gm.

title: mexican corn and rice
directions: Cook rice as package directs.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish, well-buttered.
Put corn on top of rice, then the undiluted soup. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice cocktail and pineapple juice with sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Refrigerate ginger ale overnight.
Mix altogether just before serving.
An ice ring made of cranberry juice cocktail is great to add to the punch just before serving too.

title: lolly's peanut butter fudge
directions: Prepare a 9 x 13-inch pan by greasing bottom lightly.
Mix together peanut butter, Marshmallow Fluff, flour, vanilla and walnuts.
Set aside.

title: baked salmon
directions: Melt butter in glass
pie
plate; add salmon, milk, egg and bread.
Stir with fork to mix and moisten all ingredients. Smooth with fork.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: nanny's peanut butter candy
directions: Stir together sugar, corn syrup and milk.
Put in skillet and cook on stove top.

Cook mixture, stirring frequently to prevent sticking, for approximately 30 minutes on medium heat or until you can drop some of mixture into a cup of water and it can be formed into a ball without being very sticky to fingers.
When ready, remove from heat and put in peanut butter, margarine or butter and vanilla.
Beat quickly until all ingredients are mixed.
Mixture will start to set up quickly.
Before it sets up, pour it into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: pineapple hawaiian
directions: You will need an ice cream scooper, measuring spoons and 4 serving plates.

title: cobbler with pears 'n cranberries
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pan.
In medium pan, combine the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in cranberries.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes or until cranberries pop open.
Stir in pears.
Pour into pan.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in oats; mix well.
Add egg, mixing until moist.
Crumble over fruit.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts and wash the breasts.
Roll them in crushed croutons and arrange in greased baking dish.
Top with slices of Swiss cheese.
Combine soup and wine.
Spoon over chicken, then sprinkle remaining crushed croutons over all. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: jade tree chicken
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons of soy sauce, 1 tablespoon of oil, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, garlic powder, sugar and red pepper.
Add chicken and marinate 30 minutes in refrigerator.
In wok or electric frying pan, heat 2 tablespoons of oil on medium heat.
Cook all vegetables until tender-crisp and remove from pan.
Add chicken and marinade to same pan and cook until chicken is opaque.
Return vegetables to pan.
Mix 3 tablespoons of soy sauce, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, lemon juice and water.
Pour over vegetables and chicken and simmer until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: egg souffle
directions: The night before:
Cut sausage links into 4 pieces; cook until brown.
Drain and set aside.
Combine eggs, milk and dry mustard. Layer croutons, cheese, sausage and egg mixture in buttered (Pam) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: frozen strawberry cream
directions: Stir together flour, brown sugar, nuts and oleo; spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spread 2/3 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save the rest.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular baking pan or 2 (8 or 9-inch) round layer pans.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all together; place in bake and serve dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with butter crackers (Keebler Town House Crackers).

title: brisket
directions: Wrap brisket in foil with seasonings.
Pour liquid smoke on and wrap tight.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Melt oleo.
Add flour and pecans.
Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Blend pudding with milk for 2 minutes.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Chill.

title: spice bars
directions: Stirring constantly, boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool to almost room temperature (must be cool so the flour won't lump).
Add 1 t baking soda and 2 1/2 c flour; stir well.
Pour batter onto greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350 F for 20-25 minutes. (Less time for thin bars).

title: fried cabbage
directions: Remove fat from pork before cooking.
Place in sealable container with the meat tenderizer, salt, pepper, basil, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, cider vinegar and minced garlic. Seal container and marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Mix together soup, milk and rice in large baking dish with half of the onion soup.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Add remaining onion soup.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: ghoorabie (cookies)(international:  egypt)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Alternately add flour and flavoring until dough is cookie dough texture.
Moisten hands with milk and shape cookies to bite-sized pieces, arranging on cookie sheet, 1/4-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until pink around edges. Remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.
Colored sugar can be used for the holidays.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Fold broccoli into combined mixture.
Place in a buttered casserole, 9 x 13-inches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli (omit salt).
Saute celery and onion in butter or margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz to broccoli, then add soup and other ingredients.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cayenne cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl beat eggs; add corn, cheese, cornmeal, sugar, soda, cayenne pepper and sour cream.
Mix well. Melt butter and stir into batter.
In a 10-inch cast-iron skillet or 9-inch square baking pan, place remaining butter.
Heat pan in oven until butter melts.
Immediately pour batter into pan and bake 25 minutes or until firm and golden brown.

title: canned sweet potatoes
directions: Boil the sugar and water; let cool.
Put sweet potatoes in jars and pour cold sugar water over them.
Seal in jars and boil 2 hours.
(Five quarts of water and 3 cups sugar will fill 10 quarts of sweet potatoes.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Toss sour cream and
Cool
Whip
over remaining ingredients. Stir in cherries (optional).

title: paradise jam
directions: Cook pears in large pan for 3 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients and bring to boil.
Stir in sugar.
Bring to boil and boil hard for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in pectin. Stir for 5 minutes to cool slightly (to prevent fruit from floating).
Ladle into jars.
Makes 8 1/2 pints.

title: chocolate peanut butter crispies
directions: Melt in the microwave the chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and oil on High, stirring occasionally, until melted and smooth. Gently stir in cereal and 1/2 cup dates, nuts or whatever you prefer.
Press mixture in lightly greased pan.
Chill until set, then cut into bars.

title: family style meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Shape into loaf and place in Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix jello, pineapple and sugar together in saucepan and bring to
a
boil;
remove
from
heat.
Add cream cheese and water; blend
well.
Chill
until almost firm.
Fold in Dream Whip and cover with nuts; chill.
Jello mold may be used.

title: cocoa devil's food cake with peppermint frosting
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add soft shortening and water. Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup water; beat 2 more minutes. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add egg mixture gradually.
Add squash and mix well. Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into two greased loaf pans and bake at 325° until done.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set in refrigerator.
(Note: If you process the ingredients, omit parsley).
Bring the salsa to a boil and simmer about 20 minutes.
Pour into hot jars, adjust caps; process 30 minutes.
Makes about 6 half pints.

title: jellied pineapple and cucumber salad
directions: Thoroughly drain pineapples, mashing fruit down to the syrup; add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
In a small saucepan, heat syrup to boiling.
In a medium mixing bowl, turn the gelatin and add the hot syrup and stir until dissolved.
Add salt and lemon juice and sour cream and beat until smooth.
Stir in pineapple and cucumber. Chill until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Place bread cubes in a mixing bowl.
Pour butter over the cubes; toss until coated.
Add sugar, eggs, milk and pineapple. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes, until firm and brown.
(Microwave directions; 15 to 20 minutes.)
Serve warm or cold.

title: oscar's griddle cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine wet ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
After mixing, let sit for five minutes.
Pour on heated and buttered (or margarined or cooking sprayed) pan.
Flip as bubbles burst.
So good you will want to double recipe and use again the following day.

title: praline bars
directions: Cover cookie pan (one with sides) with aluminum foil.
Lightly grease bottom of foil.
Layer bottom with uncrushed graham crackers.
Melt butter and chocolate bark in small saucepan, and add 1 cup light brown sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Pour and spread evenly over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350 degrees.
Melt chocolate bark and spoon over cookies.
Cut while warm.
These are extra easy and delicious, too. Makes 24 bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix in order as listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Heat broiler.
Place peppers in baking pan under broiler for about 20 minutes, turning every 5 minutes or so until peppers are evenly charred.
Remove and let stand until cool enough to handle. Peppers will be easy to peel.
Peel and discard skin.
Remove and discard inner seeds and core.
Thickly slice peppers and set aside.

title: mac and spice cheese
directions: Bring 4 cups water to boiling; add macaroni and cook until tender.
Rinse under warm water.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine milk, eggs, diced cheese, green peppers, tomatoes and bacon bits.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fish and chips casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk and tuna; bring to boil.
Stir in cooked noodles, cheese, mushrooms and olives.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Take cream cheese out 1 hour before mixing.
Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese; blend well and add all other ingredients except nuts.
Chill 30 minutes.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts and refrigerate 12 hours.

title: brillant candy slices
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, creaming well.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour.
Mix well; stir in pecan halves and candied cherries.
Chill 1 hour.
Divide in thirds.
Shape in rolls 10-inches long.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Cut into 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes until delicately browned on the edges.

title: creamed corn
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Beat and add milk.
Add corn.
Bake for one hour at 350° or until custard is set.

title: moon cake
directions: In saucepan, bring water and oleo to a boil. Add flour and stir.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Place on a greased jelly roll pan and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Way bars in milk.
Mix with condensed milk.
Cool. Fold in Cool Whip.
Finish filling freezer with whole milk.
Makes 4 quarts.
Freeze in ice cream freezer until firm.

title: egg noodles
directions: Put egg yolks and water in bowl.
Mix together.
Add flour. May require more flour until dough is not sticky.
Roll out thin and let dry, then cut into strips.
Cook in chicken broth about 5 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: In large mixing bowl of electric mixer, combine Eagle Brand milk, ReaLime juice and Cool Whip.
Beat thoroughly.
Add green food coloring, mix well.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Pierce potatoes and arrange in oven.
Cook on Full power for 10 to 14 minutes or until done.
Turn potatoes over halfway through cooking time.
Set aside to cool.
Melt butter in casserole dish. Stir in flour, chives, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 5 to 8 minutes or until thickened.
Stir occasionally during cooking time.
Stir in cheese.
Slice potatoes and add to sauce.
Heat, covered, thoroughly.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix milk and chips; put on low heat. Stir until melted, then add nuts.
Spread in pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 450° in greased cake pan.

title: shrimp salad mold
directions: Heat soup and cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup mixture.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased individual salad molds. Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 10.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make a thick white sauce by melting fat.
Add flour and combine thoroughly.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste; cook on low heat until thick.
Combine white sauce, 1 cup grated cheese, almonds, Worcestershire sauce, 1 teaspoon salt, black pepper and red pepper.
Place asparagus in buttered baking dish and pour the sauce mixture over it.
Top with remaining cup of grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop on cookie sheet by tablespoon (or ice cream scoop to make large cookies).
Bake 325° for 10 - 12 minutes.
Makes 4 - 6 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, shortening and peanut butter. Add eggs and vanilla and beat. Blend in dry ingredients, mix well. Roll into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork. Bake at 375 for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 3 layer lasagne
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer meat, sauce, cheese and noodles ending with 3 noodles on top.
Continue layering next two; cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: stove top scalloped potatoes
directions: In iron skillet, lightly brown potatoes and onions.
When brown as desired, sprinkle enough flour to lightly coat potatoes. Fold in enough milk to cover all.
Bring to light boiling stage. Cover with lid and simmer until tender.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Mix together a small amount of cinnamon and white sugar and sprinkle on top before baking. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugars; add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape into balls, flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add to broccoli.
Mix in mushroom soup and cheese; cook over low heat until cheese is melted and well blended.
A squeeze of lemon juice helps to retain the green color.
Serve in a chafing dish with white corn chips, tostados or Melba rounds.

title: quick cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Add 1 can frosting. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° in a Bundt pan.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter and put in bottom of dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread over graham crackers.
In a large bowl, mix together jello, hot water and cold water, crushed pineapple and oranges. Add to jello mixture and add orange sherbet.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry in paper towel.
Place in bowl. Add all other ingredients.
Let set no less than 1hour.
Serve with crackers (various flavors).

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: best doggone pancakes
directions: Combine milk, oil and egg and beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir to make a smooth batter.
Grease griddle and cook over low heat.
Makes 9 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: chocolate layer delight cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, butter and 3/4 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix in saucepan 1 cup sugar, flour, milk and egg yolks.
Bring to a boil; cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and 1 teaspoon flavoring; mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: easy hearty tomato soup
directions: Mix together and heat. Serve with cubed garlic toast topped with shredded cheese.

title: tamale perfect pie
directions: Brown meats together with the vegetables (onion, celery and pepper) until meat is brown and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add tomatoes, corn, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Cover and boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Combine orange, lemon, pineapple and apple juices.
Chill for 1 hour; then add soda.

title: idaho crayfish creole
directions: Clean the crawfish by tearing off the tails and removing the meat inside.
Wash them in cold water and set them aside to drain. Cut the celery, onion, peppers and tomatoes, then set aside.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together well with a fork.
Pour mixture over bubbling margarine.
Do not stir.
Add hot fruit over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Batter will rise to the top, forming a delicious crust.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Cut in the butter with a knife.
Arrange apple slices in a Pam-sprayed pie plate. Sprinkle above mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.
Rhubarb, peaches or bananas may be substituted for the apples.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and margarine.
Cook and let come to a boil. Pour into eggs and stir rapidly.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: wedding punch-red
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Chill when ready to serve.
Add sherbet and 7 - up.
Yield: 60 servings.

title: twenty-four hour slaw
directions: Layer onions and cabbage alternately in a deep bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients except oil in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in salad oil.
Pour evenly over vegetables.
Do not stir.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 13 baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place popcorn in very large bowl.
In saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt.
Cook, uncovered, stirring often, until hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Slowly pour syrup over popcorn; toss until coated.
With buttered fingers, shape into 16 balls.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small pan, fry bacon till clear. Add margarine and all other ingredients, except shrimp. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place shrimp in open baking dish and pour liquid over shrimp.
Stir to coat all shrimp.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes, stirring twice.
Serve hot.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, cream cheese and soft oleo well.
Add powdered sugar and milk.
Mix all well.
Fold in whipped topping. Place in crust.
Top with chopped or shredded Hershey bar or chocolate chips.
Or top by drizzling on chocolate sauce.
Freeze and thaw slightly before serving.

title: chocolate-peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet. Cream the butter and peanut butter with sugars. Add egg and vanilla.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Stir in crispy rice cereal and chocolate pieces.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned.
Let stand 1 minute on baking sheet before removing.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: two-cheese appetizers
directions: Knead together in bowl 1 1/2 cups Swiss cheese and next 6 ingredients.
Form into ball and chill 15 minutes.
Divide dough in 6 equal pieces.
Shape each piece into rope 6-inches long.
Put ropes parallel to each other and cut ropes in 1/2-inch pieces. Shape each piece into a ball and flatten into a circle about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange on baking sheet, leaving 2 inch space between.
Brush with egg beaten with 1 teaspoon water.
Sprinkle each with a little of the remaining Swiss cheese.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes, or until puffed and lightly browned.
Cool on rack.
Sprinkle with paprika and store in airtight container. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chocolate festival cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, cocoa, sour cream and vanilla; beat on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Add flour and eggs; beat well. Pour into Chocolate Crumb Crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Without opening oven, reduce temperature to 250°; continue baking 30 minutes (cheesecake may not appear set in middle).
Turn off oven; leave cheesecake in oven for 30 minutes without opening door. Remove from oven.
With knife, loose cake from side of pan.
Cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except oats in saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add oats. Stir until mixed well. Spoon on to waxed paper. Let cool.

title: herbed cauliflower casserole
directions: Wash and break cauliflower into flowerets.
Cook in a small amount of boiling, salted water about 10 minutes.
Drain. Place in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.

title: stuffed avocados
directions: Peel and slice avocado in half; remove seed.
Sprinkle with lemon juice so the avocado meat will not darken as quickly.
Fill the cavity with the artichoke heart.
Top each avocado half with 1 to 2 tablespoons of the Horsey Sauce (recipe in this book).
Makes 1/2 avocado per person.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat shortening over low heat until melted; remove from heat.
Mix in brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Rich and chewy.

title: decorating frosting
directions: Measure shortening in mixing bowl; add sugar and water.
Mix with spatula until well blended, then start mixing on low speed for 1 or 2 minutes.
Mix on high speed until smooth and creamy. Add a few drops of water at a time until good spreading consistency.
Stiff icing does better for decorating.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Whip soup and cheese together to make smooth.
Drain asparagus.
In a casserole put a layer of asparagus and layer soup and cheese mix.
Layer cracker crumbs and chopped eggs.
Keep repeating layers.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
When you remove from oven, slice egg on top and sprinkle with paprika.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry bell pepper, celery and onion in butter.
Add tomato sauce, water, garlic salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add bay leaf to sauce.
Cook slowly 40 to 45 minutes on low heat.
Last 20 to 25 minutes, drop in shrimp.
Serve with rice.

title: fried herring(much eaten in scotland.)
directions: Clean herrings; roll in raw oatmeal with salt and fry.

title: french onion soup(2 servings)
directions: Chop onions.
Put in pot with a little oil to brown.
Once onions are brown, add 2 cups water and the bouillon cubes.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes. Then put this soup mixture in your bowls.
Add the bread and put the Mozzarella cheese on top of each.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Enjoy!!

title: vege links sandwich spread
directions: Brown Vege Links in butter and let cool.
In large bowl, mash links until the texture is like small curd cottage cheese.
Add onions, mayonnaise, eggs and relish.
Mix well.
May add additional mayonnaise for a moister spread.

title: chocolate bark bake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand.
Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add chocolate.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with oats.
Stir in vanilla, raisins and nuts. Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package instructions.
Rinse in cold water.
Combine vegetables and stir into drained spaghetti. Pour salad dressing over mixture, blending well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook sliced potatoes in bacon grease and water to cover until tender.
Add green beans the last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking time. Drain.
Add bacon pieces and dressing.
Mix only until combined. Serve hot.

title: sunday morning bloody mary
directions: Chill Bloody Mary mix prior to putting in thermos.
Serve with pickles or celery.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: white fruit salad
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and vinegar in double boiler until thick. Add marshmallows and gelatin.
Remove from fire and stir until marshmallows begin to melt.
Add pineapple, cherries, fruit cocktail, pecans and whipped cream.
Let set in cool place.
Slice and serve on lettuce for salad with whipped cream for dessert.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes and onion until tender in boiling water. Drain.
Mash until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Cool and put in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: crab canapes
directions: Unroll dough and separate into 12 rounds.
Divide each round in half to make 24 rounds.
Fit into bottom and sides of greased mini muffin pans; set aside.

title: orange-cranberry relish
directions: Squeeze juice from oranges; refrigerate in covered container for other use.
Remove pulp from orange peels; discard.
Cut peels in quarters; finely grind in food processor.
Add half the cranberries and continue processing until ground.
Repeat with remaining cranberries.
In 3-quart bowl, mix cranberries, sugar and ginger.
Stir in pecans.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: fried green beans
directions: Saute onions and ham in oil.
Add beans to skillet and stir; turn heat low and simmer 30 minutes.

title: deer stew
directions: You will need 1 large pot sprayed good.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Peel apples; cut in quarters.
Put in a baking dish, standing on sides in rows.
Mix sugars and spice together; sprinkle over apples.
Cut margarine into dots; put over apples.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole with Pam.
Pour in bean mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup together and cook 4 minutes at 100% power.
Add peanuts, stir and cook 4 minutes at 100% power.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend and cook at 100% power; add baking soda, stir and pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, butter and pecans.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then cool.
Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread onto baked layer after the baked layer has cooled.
Spread cherry pie filling on the top.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, evaporated milk and vanilla. Fill container with whole milk.
Yields one gallon.

title: baked scallops
directions: Melt butter.
Add crumbs and garlic. Brown lightly. Stir in parsley.
Put 1/2 of this mixture into bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan. Pour lemon juice over crumbs.
Add scallops and spread rest of mixed crumbs on top of scallops.
Dot with butter.

title: hot pickles
directions: Put garlic and dill in bottom of jars; pack with cut up cucumbers tight in jars.
Boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pour in jar, seal and set in sun for 14 days.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: In skillet, melt margarine.
Spread sauerkraut over melted margarine, sprinkle with rice, then onion.
Top all with ground beef, salt, pepper, mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Cook, covered, over low heat 25 to 30 minutes or until rice and beef are done. Serve from skillet. Yields:
4 to 5 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Thaw and drain well the peas.
Combine all ingredients, except peas.
Mix well, then combine peas and stir in.
Chill.

title: whole corn bread
directions: Combine corn, sour cream and eggs.
Beat soft margarine and muffin mix together and add to corn mixture.
Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: court bouillon
directions: Dissolve flour in 4 cups of water, then alternate with layers of seasoning and fish, pouring flour over each layer.
Continue until all fish and seasoning have been used.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch bits and butter, then add all the other ingredients.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not overbake.

title: date nut harvest cake
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over chopped dates, baking soda and chopped apples.
Mix well and cool.
Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs; add vanilla.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with date mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: I place
all the dry ingredients together in a bowl; as I add each
liquid, I continue to mix with my electric mixer. It will be	quite
dark
and very runny.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°, depending on your oven 35 to 40 minutes or longer.

title: zucchini pocket
directions: Combine ingredients and toss lightly to mix.
Wrap and seal in a foil pocket and grill.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook white syrup, sugar and water until 230°.
Add peanuts. Cook until 300°;
remove from stove.
Add butter, vanilla, salt and soda.
Stir quickly.

title: cheese-frosted cauliflower
directions: Remove	leaves, trim base from cauliflower and place on rack to	steam
over
boiling
water
in a 12-inch Dutch oven. After steaming,
place cauliflower in cake pan. Sprinkle with salt. Drain oven and heat for baking.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard. Spread
over cauliflower.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake in Dutch oven in cake
pan
until
cheese
is
melted and bubbly.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pickles
directions: Peel and take out seeds of pickles.
Cut in strips and/or chunks.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Cold pack 10 minutes.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 cup cheese and onion.
Set aside.
Combine soups and enchilada sauce.
Dip tortillas in hot oil to soften, a few seconds on each side.
Top each tortilla with 1 heaping tablespoonful of meat mixture; roll up.
Place, seam side down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over and top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.
Refrigerate unused portion in airtight container.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients; reserve 1/4 cup to coat berries.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs one at a time; add almond flavoring.
Mix in dry ingredients and fold in berries, coated with mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook ground beef, onions, green pepper and garlic until meat browns.
Drain off fat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Pour boiling water over blossoms.
Let stand overnight.
Drain in the morning.
Add sugar, lemons and orange.
Add yeast cake. Let stand for 10 days, then bottle.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Roll wings in melted butter, then in bread crumbs mixture.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Chop the dried beef into small pieces.
Combine cheese and beef.
Add small amounts of green onions and olives, according to your own taste. Form into a ball.

title: chicken divan
directions: Remove chicken from bone in large pieces and put in buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with broccoli spears.
Prepare gravy mix as directed.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with pieces of cheese, then noodles.
Bake in 350°
oven for 25 minutes.

title: grandma's corn fritters
directions: Heat shortening to 375°. Drop by spoonfuls into shortening. Fry 3 to 4 minutes until golden brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, then milk and vanilla.
Beat until nearly smooth.

In small bowl, stir together 1 3/4 cups flour and baking powder and then add this to mixture in the medium size bowl; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened (batter will be lumpy). Toss berries with remaining 1 tablespoon of flour.
Fold into the batter.
Use muffin papers or grease muffin tins.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake for 25 minutes or until evenly browned.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Mix together with au gratin potatoes (add ingredients according to their directions) and package of vegetables.
Bake according to directions on potatoes.

title: holiday chocolate berry trifle
directions: Pour cold milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Gently stir in 2 cups whipped topping. Place half of the brownie cubes in 2-quart serving bowl. Top with half of the pudding mixture, half of the raspberries and 2 cups whipped topping. Repeat layers. Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve. Makes 12 servings.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans and set aside.
Blend all ingredients, and pour into prepared cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
After cake cools, slice each layer in two to make four layers.

title: cocoa kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar, a few tablespoons at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in cocoa.
Line cookie sheet with brown paper and drop batter with teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in oven preheated to 275° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool before removing from pans.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: strawberry cream cookies
directions: Note:
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: spanish rice
directions: In oil, fry rice, stirring constantly until rice is brown. Season with garlic salt, pepper, etc.
Stir-fry the onion and pepper (optional) with rice until flavor is absorbed.
While rice and ingredients are frying, fry sausage until brown and well done. Mix sausage into rice; add tomato sauce and water.
Stir rice lightly and cook at medium heat until water is all absorbed from rice and you can see the rice (dry).
Do not stir rice while water is absorbing or it will become soggy.
When all water is absorbed, cover rice tightly and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir rice from the bottom.
Simmer 15 minutes more and stir again.
Take off heat. Serve.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat strawberries and sugar over stove long enough to melt sugar.
Add jello.
Mix pudding with milk.
Beat sour cream, then add Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, then strawberries and sugar and then pudding.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Crust:
Mix crackers with butter and pat in an 8 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cap the tops of the tomatoes.
Spoon out the pulp.
Leave shell 1/2 inch thick; drain.

title: doggy delights
directions: Mix all ingredients adding more milk if needed to make firm. Roll out onto a floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Use bone shaped cookie cutter, cut into shapes.
Bake on ungreased baking sheets at 350 for 30 minutes or until lightly toasted.

title: company chicken
directions: Shred beef to spread in greased baking pan.
Cut breasts in half; wrap in raw bacon.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours. Serves 2 to 4.

title: noodles - fast and delicious
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Drain noodles.
In separate pan melt margarine, add whipping cream or canned milk and just bring to a boil.
Mix in with noodles.
Fold in Parmesan cheese and serve. Can be garnished with chives or parsley.

title: sausage bread
directions: Cook sausage; drain well. Reserve 1 egg white. Mix all other ingredients. Roll out rolls (press seams together). Put 1/3 mixture down the middle of each roll, making 3 rolls. Fold over and seal seam; brush with egg white. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cone cupcakes
directions: Make cake mix according to package directions, add flour.
Put cones in muffin tins for stability, pour 2 tablespoons cake mix in each cone.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost top with favorite frosting.
Sprinkle with colored sprinkles.
A special treat for children!

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Slice cooked sweet potatoes into baking dish.
Mix salt, sugar and flour; sprinkle over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Add cream and marshmallows.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Add nuts and serve.

title: boston baked corn
directions: Combine catsup, onion, brown sugar, dry mustard and salt. Stir in the corn.
Put into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with diced, uncooked bacon.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about an hour.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Burn 1/2 cup sugar; add 1/4 cup boiling water, stirring.
Set aside to cool.
Cream 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Add 3 egg yolks, 1 cup cold water and 2 cups flour and beat.
Add well beaten egg whites and 1/2 cup flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder, 1 teaspoon vanilla and the burnt sugar.
Mix well and bake in 13 x 9-inch loaf pan.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into ball and eat.

title: spider cookies(halloween)
directions: Frost oatmeal cookie with frosting.
Arrange jelly beans on cookies to make spider head and body.
Cut 6 to 8 licorice whip pieces (about 1 1/2 inches long).
Curve and position for legs. Add red candy antennae.

title: potato latkes(pancakes)
directions: Heat butter in frying pan.
Combine all other ingredients in a bowl.
Drop the mixture into frying pan by the tablespoon.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Keep hot until all are fried.
Serve with sour cream and applesauce.
Serves 8.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients together, mixing well.
Grill chicken using sauce to baste chicken.
Sauce will do 5 to 6 chicken halves.

title: cheese cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake bread in it for 20 minutes. Serves 12.

title: uglee dip
directions: Mix together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: almond joy bar cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and remove from oven. Combine coconut with condensed milk and spoon over top.
Bake another 20 minutes and remove from oven.
Blend sugar, butter and milk together in saucepan and bring to a boil for one minute. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until smooth.
Pour over cake immediately.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil, vanilla and zucchini and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Add nuts. Bake in three medium loaf pans (greased) at 325° for 1 hour or more, all ovens vary.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions very fine.
Pour boiling water over same.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Do this twice.
Boil 15 minutes and bottle.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Put butter in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Heat the molasses to the boiling point, then pour it over the butter.
Mix the dry ingredients and sift together.
Add butter and molasses.
Chill mixture thoroughly.
Place 1/4 of the mixture on a floured board and roll as thin as possible.
Cut shapes with a small round cutter that has been dipped in flour.
Roll the trimmings in with the next 1/4 of the dough.
Keeps remaining dough chilled.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes until crisp.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Pour over pork chops and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Combine oleo, sugars, eggs and peanut butter to make creamy. Add soda, vanilla, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Mix well and spoon by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cook all at once or store cookie dough in fridge and bake as needed.
(Watch out for monsters who eat your dough before they are baked.)
This recipe will make 20 to 24 dozen cookies if you ever get them baked and counted before the monsters get to them.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Mix together milk, lemon juice and 2 egg yolks.
Beat egg whites into the mixture.
Chop the strawberries and add to mixture.
Crush vanilla wafers.
Place a layer in bowl, then a layer of mixture.
Repeat until all is used.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve in sherbet dishes and garnish with whole strawberries.

title: soy oat waffles
directions: Soak soy beans several hours or overnight in sufficient water to keep covered.
Drain; discard water.
(These beans may be stored in refrigerator or frozen for use at a moment's notice.)

title: microwave peanut brittle(total cook time: 10 minutes)
directions: Prepare a cookie sheet, well buttered, or you can use a Teflon coated pan.

title: my grandmother's salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Put all fruit, cheese and Cool Whip in bowl.
Put dry Jell-O on top and mix well.

title: wild rice soup
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in rice, ham, carrots, almonds and salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend in half and half and sherry.
Heat to serving temperature.
Garnish with minced parsley and chives.
Makes 6 cups.

title: oyster stuffing for turkey
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add just enough milk to make it moist.

title: florentine spaghetti
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed on package.
Brown meat; drain. Stir in herb-spice mix, tomato paste and water; bring to boil. Simmer 10 minutes.
Layer half of spaghetti, sauce, cottage cheese and spinach and Mozzarella cheese in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish; repeat layers.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab mun doo
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Put 2 teaspoons filling in each pie center.
Moisten edges and seal.
Deep fry to a golden brown.
Makes about 30.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except sugar, then sprinkle the sugar over top.
Cover container and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Mix well and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Grease a baking dish the size for your need.
Peel and cut into bite size as many potatoes as you need.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle to taste with salt, pepper and garlic.
Chop the onion and toss with potatoes.
Dot with butter; cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir potatoes and microwave until potatoes are done.

title: fresh apple dessert
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and beat.
Add and mix apples and nuts.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix all together and bake at 350° until done (approximately 30 minutes).
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Serve warm or cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook noodles per directions.
Layer ingredients, 1/2 noodles, 1 can tomato soup and 1 can mushroom soup.
Top with ground beef.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese slices before serving.
Serve with bread and salad.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; boil over moderate heat 5 minutes.
Remove; stir in chocolate, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until well blended.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch greased pan; cool to room temperature.
Cut small squares; makes 3 pounds.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Slip off skins.
Combine rest of ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add beets and simmer 5 more minutes.
Pack beets into hot jars, fill with syrup and seal.

title: butterflake rolls
directions: Soften yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in warm water.
Blend in 1 cup of flour; let rise until light and bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes. Cream oleomargarine in bowl; add 1/4 cup sugar, salt and egg yolks. Mix well and add to yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add 3 cups flour gradually.
Knead 36 strokes.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled, approximately 45 minutes.
Divide in half. Roll each half into 18 x 6-inch rectangle.
Spread center third with butter, fold one side over butter and spread with butter. Fold opposite side to overlap center.
Cut into 1-inch strips. Coil strips on well-greased baking sheet.
Let rise until light. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
In a separate bowl, sift together next five ingredients, then add to carrot mixture. Add four eggs one at a time.
Pour into 2 greased cake pans and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together well.
Sprinkle in pudding mix and stir.
Chill.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix the Jell-O and Kool-Aid in the hot water until dissolved. Mix in the cold water.
Fill up popsicle holders and freeze.

title: honey barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: braised rabbit in wine sauce
directions: Roll rabbit pieces in flour.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Saute in skillet with margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and let simmer over low heat until tender. Usually takes 1 hour. (You may need to add more water as it cooks.)
Same recipe used for quail.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice meat into pieces 1/4-inch thick.
Dust with seasoned flour and brown in melted butter.
Remove meat.
In same skillet, saute onion and garlic.
Add mushrooms and saute until tender. Add both soups, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Stir in the meat.
Cover and simmer until tender.
(Sirloin will take about 15 to 20 minutes.
Round or chuck longer.)
When meat is tender, add sour cream and heat until hot.
Serve over noodles.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Put in the refrigerator until chilled. Then serve.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove the crusts from bread and set aside.
Arrange bread slices in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken. Cover with the mushrooms and water chestnuts.
In a bowl beat eggs, blend in milk, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange cheese on top.
Combine soups and pimentos and pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking crumble crusts. Toss with melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: choco-banana flip
directions: Place half each of the milk, bananas, chocolate syrup, vanilla and ice cream.
Put into electric blender.
Cover and process until smooth.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookies and slightly overlap on a 13-inch pizza pan. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cookies run together to form a crust. Allow to cool.

title: sally's beef dish
directions: Do not dilute soups; stir all together in heavy baking dish. Cover; bake at 250° to 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: onion burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape into four patties. Grill, uncovered over medium heat. Serve on buns.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pat into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Drain. Yields 6 servings.

title: bavarian cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl by hand.
Form into balls and flatten on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread your uncooked ground beef.
On top of this, spread the can of celery soup.
The next layer is the milk.
Place cheese slices and onion on top of milk.
Top all off with the Tater Tots.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: apple bundles
directions: Cut apple slices in half.
Unroll dough and separate into 8 triangles.
Place a few apple slices at the wide end of crescent roll dough triangle and roll tightly.
Arrange bundles in a well greased baking dish.
pour mountain dew into corner of baking dish but not over bundles.
Drizzle melted butter on top of bundles. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add rest of pineapple juice. Add frozen berries and pineapple.
Pour half into mold and refrigerate to set, about 1 hour.
Take 1/2 pint of sour cream and spread over jello.
Take remaining jello and put on top.
Put back in refrigerator to set.
Top with Cool Whip.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour into a baked pie crust.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and microwave on High power for 5 minutes.
Stir well. Cook 5 minutes more.
Add chocolate chips and marshmallows. Mix well until chips and marshmallows are melted.
Add vanilla and mix well. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Nuts may be added if desired.
You may also substitute peanut butter chips for the chocolate chips, if you like.

title: pumpkin-spice bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5 x 3 inch) loaf pans.
In large bowl mix together first 6 ingredients.
Stir together pumpkin and corn oil.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Make well in center of flour mixture.
Add pumpkin mixture; stir just until flour is moistened.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center come out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.
Remove; cool on racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown meat & pepper in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Pour into 9x13 pan. Add noodles.
Mix with sauce.
Cover with cheese. Bake 375° for 45 mins.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix milk, pineapple, lemon juice and pecans by hand well.
Pour 1/2 of ingredients into crust.
Add Cool Whip to top of mixture. Top with 1 layer of bananas.
Repeat.
Chill 3 hours.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
You can use peas and carrots for color instead of just peas.

title: squash and zucchini salad
directions: Dice squash and zucchini. Add all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
In skillet, heat oil and butter.
Add meat and brown over high heat.
Place browned meat in slow cooker.
Sprinkle with tapioca.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Cover slow cooker and cook on high 3 to 4 hours or on low 7 to 8 hours.
Serve with French or Italian bread and salad.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Beat sugar, butter and Crisco until smooth.
Add 1 ounce water to milk to make 5 ounces and stir.
Gradually add milk and vanilla.
Add dash of salt and continue beating until smooth.
Ice the cake.
Heat 1 can chocolate frosting in microwave about 1 minute.
Stir and pour over frosting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine gelatin and water in a medium saucepan over medium heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat; allow to cool.
In a chilled medium bowl, whip cream until stiff.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Fold whipped cream into cream cheese mixture.
Fold in gelatin.
Spoon filling evenly into cooked cooled pie crust.
Cover and refrigerate until pie is set in center.
Arrange strawberries over filling.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add dates, nuts and sugar.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until browned. Cut in bars while still warm; roll in powdered sugar.

title: baked chicken in its own gravy
directions: Coat chicken with flour. Arrange chicken in single layer with skin down in melted butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ritz pecan pie
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs.
Mix with 1/3 cup sugar and pecans. Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 1/3 cup sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
Combine with the dry mixture and pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.
Chill immediately.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Cook your beef, pepper and onion together and drain.
Add garlic powder, mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, soup can of water, tomatoes and Chili-O mix.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over Doritos chips.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Put chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables, 1/2 c. cheese, 1/2 c. onions, soup and milk.
Bake at 375° for 20 mins.
Place crescent rolls in strips.
Bake 15 mins. longer.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions on top.
Bake 3-5 mins. longer.

title: persian delight
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup flour.
Add 1/2 chopped pecans. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Better under than overdone.
Cream cream cheese, powdered sugar and whipped cream.
Layer on top of the 1st layer. Mix puddings with milk until stiff.
Spread on top of 2nd layer. Spread the balance of the whipped cream over all.
Dust with chopped pecans.
Delicious!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 9X13 inch dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Let sit 10-15 minutes before serving.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain and put fruit in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight. Blend cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
Add a little more Cool Whip if creamier consistency is needed.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage in
heavy skillet.
Transfer sausage to 2 quart greased casserole
dish.
In
sausage
drippings,
saute celery, onion, green
peppers
and	mushrooms
until
lightly browned. Transfer to
casserole
dish.
Add	water chestnuts, rice, broth and 1 can
of
chicken
(or equivalent of 2 cups); mix well. Cover and bake at
350° for 1 hour or until rice is fluffy and tender.

title: thelma's homemade noodles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough out real thin.
Then roll dough up like a jelly roll.
Cut slices real thin.
Sprinkle with flour.
Cook beef with 2 teaspoons vinegar, garlic salt, pepper and salt as desired.
Add noodles.

title: corn dog batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Should be the consistency of honey.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter and combine all three soups and rice in a casserole dish.
Cook uncovered for 30-45 minutes on 350 degrees.

title: mandarin orange whip
directions: You will need mixer, large spoon and big bowl.

title: grandma's date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let cool.
Mix other ingredients and add dates.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, until done.
Bake in loaf pan.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook chicken and cut into small pieces.
Cook and drain broccoli as directed.
Mix chicken, soup, onion, sour cream and broccoli.
Mix well until blended.
In casserole, melt 1/2 stick butter.
Sprinkle bottom heavy with dressing, then spoon on chicken mixture.
Sprinkle more dressing, then dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a big pot.
Add two quarts of water. Bring to a boil, turn down and simmer until done.
Serves about 10 to 12.

title: white boiled icing
directions: Combine sugar, water, cream of tartar and salt in a saucepan. Cook, covered, for 3 minutes.
Remove cover and cook to soft ball stage (242°) on candy thermometer.
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites until stiff (not dry).
Slowly add hot syrup to egg whites, beating at high speed all the time.
Beat until it holds straight peaks.
May add coconut for coconut cake.

title: cornflake balls
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Stir in peanut butter and blend well.
Pour sugar, syrup and peanut butter mixture over cornflakes.
Work into balls.

title: cucumber lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and beat with cream cheese and Miracle Whip.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to jello mixture.
Mold to set. Serves 8 to 10.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and shape into 1-inch meatballs. Brown meatballs in vegetable oil.
Add green and red peppers and mushrooms.
Cook until vegetables are semi-tender; add pineapple. In separate bowl, mix 1/2 cup reserved pineapple juice with brown sugar, soy sauce, cornstarch, vinegar and water.
Pour over meatballs and vegetables.
Cook until thickened.
Divide portions equally and serve each over 1/2 cup cooked rice.

title: rabbit salad
directions: Grate the carrots.
Add the remaining ingredients.
