title: crab meat mixture
directions: In bowl combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mayonnaise, onion, garlic salt and crab meat.
Mix well. Spread in a shallow serving dish.
Pour chili sauce over crab mixture.
Garnish with parsley.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with crackers.

title: anytime quiche
directions: Bake pie shells until crisp.
Divide ingredients between shells.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until clear and drain. Sprinkle onion in pie shells; sprinkle spinach over onion and season spinach to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheeses and bacon over onion and spinach.
Beat eggs and milk; add salt, pepper and parsley and pour over other ingredients.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until center is set.
May be frozen. Makes 2 quiche.

title: tangy vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and spread in baking dish.
Reserve some for top crust, if desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In two-quart casserole dish, mix the ground beef, green beans, mushroom soup and water.
Top with single layer of Tater Tots.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix
ground beef, egg, onion, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and 1/2 tomato sauce.
Shape into a loaf.
Mix remaining tomato sauce and
other
ingredients.
Pour
over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook celery, pepper and onions in half the butter until tender, not brown.
Add garlic and ham.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Add remaining butter, shrimp, salt, Tabasco, Worcestershire and sugar. Cook, tossing often with fork until shrimp are pink.
Add tomatoes; simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes.
Stir in rice; serve.
Serves 8.

title: green pepper stew
directions: Heat oil and brown meat.
Add tomatoes, green peppers, onions, carrots, salt, pepper and water.
Cook on high until starts to boil, then turn burner to low and add bouillon cubes and bay leaves.
Simmer for about 2 hours.
Serve over rice or hot noodles.

title: shrimp rice
directions: Clean and boil shrimp; add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook rice; when done add 1 stick butter and mix.
Saute onions, celery, and bell peppers.
Add soups, shrimp, and rice.
Mix well; put in baking dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: water chestnut appetizers
directions: Combine soy sauce and 1 cup of sugar, mixing well. Soak water chestnuts in mixture for 30 minutes and drain. Roll water chestnuts in remaining 1 cup of sugar. Cut bacon strips in half. Wrap a bacon strip around each water chestnut and secure with a toothpick. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cover with foil and refrigerate until serving time. Broil 5 minutes before serving. Makes 60 appetizers.

title: carrot and celery soup
directions: Cook all ingredients in water to cover until done.
Strain and blend in a blender.
Serve.

title: cheesy winter mix
directions: Place frozen vegetables in casserole dish. Sprinkle salt and pepper. Microwave on High 3 minutes.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add softened butter.
Mix and roll into small balls.
Put on wax paper and set in refrigerator until balls are firm.

title: marinated shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni shells as package directs; rinse and drain.
In small jar with tight fitting lid or cruet, combine oil, lemon juice concentrate, salad dressing mix and horseradish; shake well. In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except lettuce.
Toss with dressing.
Cover; chill several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: english peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients with spoon.
The dough will be slightly sticky.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't overcook as they tend to burn very quickly.
Make the spoonful small as these are very sweet.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and add eggs and oil. Stir only until moistened.
Stir in strawberries and pecans.
Bake in two loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Prick the clean, dry potato a few times with a fork to allow steam to escape in baking.
Do not wrap in foil.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for about an hour.
The internal temperature should be about 210°.
This procedure produces a fluffy texture inside with a crispy skin on the outside.

title: buttermilk pecan waffles
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Beat buttermilk into egg yolks.
Add melted butter or margarine.
Combine liquid and dry ingredients; do not overstir. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; fold in pecans.
Bake in a waffle iron.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Remove sausage from casing and brown.
Break sausage as it cooks.
When browned, drain off grease and cool completely on a paper towel.

title: sesame broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling salted water, about 15 minutes or just until tender, but still crisp; drain.
In a small pan, combine oil, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and sesame seeds.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over hot broccoli, turning to coat. Serve hot.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: billie's molasses rolled cookies
directions: Combine molasses, sugar, shortening and soda in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, and boil slowly for 2 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins, sugar, water and shortening together for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
When cool, add flour and spices.
Batter is quite thin.
Bake in an oblong 13 x 9-inch pan in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
This recipe can be baked in a jelly roll pan and used as bars.

title: fitz's strawberry butter
directions: Combine all in blender or food processor with steel knife. Whip until light.
Good on popovers, pancakes, toast, etc.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sticky buns
directions: Defrost loaf of bread in refrigerator.
Cut into four lengthwise strips and each strip into 6 to 8 pieces.
Prepare three dishes for dipping; one with melted margarine, one with brown sugar and one with dry pudding.
Dip each piece of bread into each and place into greased Bundt pan which bottom has been scattered with pecan pieces.
Stack the strips and pour remaining margarine, brown sugar and pudding over them.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert over plate.
Pull apart with two forks.

title: liver and onions, italian style
directions: If necessary, remove tubes and membrane from liver. Cut liver into serving size pieces. Coat liver with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Cook onions until tender in hot oil in a large skillet. Remove onions and add liver. Brown on both sides over medium heat.
Return onions to skillet. Add the wine.
Bring to boiling and cook 1 minute. Serve at once.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Mix a little water with the cornstarch and add it and the rest of the water to the vegetables and shrimp.
Cook for 10 minutes.
If it is too thick add a little bit more water.
Add ketchup for color and Tony Chachere seasoning to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: judy's easy party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add ice and stir.
For variations and decorations, you might fix an ice ring by adding fruit, cherries and/or mint leaves to water and freeze in a jello mold.
Unmold before serving time and let float around in the punch bowl to chill punch.
Ice cubes may be made the same way.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour and chicken broth.
Add mushrooms, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Drain spaghetti.
Layer spaghetti, chicken pieces, cheese and sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage apple ring
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Press into greased ring mold (Bundt pan).
Turn over onto rack placed in shallow pan. Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in an iron skillet on top of stove or in oven.
Bake at 350° until center is done.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Mix salt, egg yolks, sour cream and flour together.
Then fold in egg whites.
Layer half the squash, egg mixture and the cheese in a casserole dish; repeat layers and sprinkle bacon and butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: impossible coconut pies
directions: Combine
eggs,
sugar,
flour and milk.
Add margarine, vanilla
and
coconut.
Beat all together.
Put margarine on 2 pie plates.
Pour
mixture
into each pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
The pie makes its own crust.
Let the pie get cold, it slices real well.
Serve cold.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add to macaroni (while still hot) cheese, milk, butter and seasonings.
Stir until cheese melts.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix by hand.
Press into wax paper-lined loaf pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple and save juice.
Bring juice to a boil and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Let cool.
Add cola, pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Chill.

title: turkey cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and roll into bite-size balls.
Place meatballs on top of broiler pan so any fat will fall through.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Use Spicy Sauce as dip for meatballs.
tags: lean ground white meat skinless turkey

title: carrot-apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth.
Stir in shredded carrots, apple, raisins and 3/4 cup pecans.
In a medium bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add this flour mixture 1/3 at a time to other mixture, mixing well.
Pour batter into two well-greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cake is done when inserted toothpick comes out clean. Cool completely.
Frost cake and garnish with pecans and carrot curls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in 2 cups of boiling water for 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Add orange (that has been cut into pieces and the membrane removed), the orange rind, sugar and Jello. Let cool and add the nuts, pineapple and celery. Pour into oblong dish and refrigerate.

title: mary ann's cheese cake
directions: Use ready made graham cracker pie shell or prepare a crust of your own.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and beaten eggs. Mix well and stir in oats.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(This makes a good substitute for pecan pie, with fewer calories.)

title: easy peanut butter blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in a 17 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish in saucepan. Combine sugar, butter, corn syrup and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Cook. Stir over medium heat until butter melts and mixture boils.
Cook (no stirring) 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Gently stir (coat).
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: vegetable chop suey
directions: Mix all the ingredients except chestnuts and bean sprouts. Cook in a large skillet about 15 minutes. Add Chinese vegetables and cook 5 minutes more. Serve with fried noodles or boiled rice.

title: sauerkraut and beef (or pork)
directions: Put 1/2 kraut in pan.
Sprinkle flour, sugar, salt and pepper over it.
Add meat, onions and apple.
Cover with rest of kraut and with boiling water.
Cover tightly and cook on low heat, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Preheat oven 375 degree.
Mix above in large bowl; mix well. Pour into large baking pan.
Cook 40 or 50 minute.
Let set 10 minute before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 15-inch pan
the first 3 ingredients. In saucepan, combine margarine and chicken broth with dressing. Mix together well.
Spoon on top of creamy chicken mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crisp pastel cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, sugar, gelatin, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Shape dough into 3/4 inch balls. Place about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 6-8 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into quarters and boil. Saute margarine, onion, flour and bell pepper in a skillet.
Add water, milk, salt and pepper.
Place cabbage quarters in a buttered casserole dish and pour soup mixture over the cabbage. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Mix soup, milk, chilies, chicken, onion and broth.
Heat thoroughly on top of stove.
Line a large casserole (9 x 13-inch) with tortilla wedges.
Layer soup mixture over tortillas and then cheese.
Repeat layers and end with cheese on top.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: pierogi
directions: Combine above ingredients and roll out as pie 1/4 at a time. Cut circles 3 to 4 inches in diameter.
Put about 1 tablespoon filling (to follow) in the center of each circle.
Fold over and dampen edges to seal.
Cook a few at a time in slow boiling water. Brown slightly in butter.
Good served with sweetened sour cream.

title: better than life cake
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar; cook until thick.
(Doesn't get real thick.)
Punch holes in cake and pour pineapple mixture over cake. Prepare pudding as directed; mix in coconut and spread over top of pineapple mixture on the cake.
Cover with Cool Whip and pecans.

title: no bake chocolate cheesecake
directions: Place chocolate chips in microwave-proof bowl.
Place in microwave for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on High until chips are melted and smooth when stirred.
Set aside to cool.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine corn muffin mix, egg, corn, Tabasco and milk.
Combine sour cream, dill, 1/2 Cheddar cheese and onions.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together and turn into a greased pie plate.
Bake
at
350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test center with toothpick.
If
pie
is
done, pick will come out clean. The pie is chewy like brownies.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix up salad to your liking.
Add meat mixture; top with Cheddar cheese and tortilla chips.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half, leave bottom in pan.
Spread mustard on rolls, sprinkle ham, cheese and onions on rolls.
Put top layer of rolls back on and bake at 375 degrees until cheese melts.

title: country pan meal
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of iron skillet or baking dish.
Slice potatoes over margarine; lightly salt and pepper.
Spread cabbage or squash over potatoes; lightly salt and pepper.
Slice onion over cabbage or squash.
Mix canned tomatoes and hamburger; lightly salt and pepper.
Cover with onion slices (entire top).
Bake at 425° for about 1 hour, or until brown.
Serve with corn muffins.

title: pecan frosting
directions: Cream the butter and 1/3 cup powdered sugar.
Add corn syrup, vanilla and salt, mixing well.
Add half and half, alternately with remaining powdered sugar, beginning and ending with sugar. Mix well after each addition.
Stir in pecans.
Yields about 1 cup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into ball.
Chill and roll into chopped nuts.

title: copper pennies
directions: Drain and cool carrots.
Combine with onions and pepper in large bowl.
Stir remaining ingredients together.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: You will need an 8-inch square dish.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large pan, cook onion and celery in oil.
Add potatoes, frozen corn and broth.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Whisk milk and flour together in small bowl.
Add to potatoes and corn mixture. Add rest of ingredients, cook till all vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oil for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes; boil until cubes dissolve.
Gradually add noodles and boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in frozen chopped broccoli, salt and garlic salt.
Cook 4 minutes, then add the milk and cheese.
Add pepper as desired.
Cook until the cheese melts.

title: apple crisp
directions: Into buttered casserole, put apples, cinnamon and water.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Blend these ingredients until they are crumbly.
Sprinkle this mixture over apples and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an ice cream freezer. Freeze.

title: pistachio florentines
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.
In a pan, gently heat butter and syrup until melted.
Stir in flour, nuts, cherries and lemon juice.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Bake at 350° for one hour and reduce heat to 225° for another hour, until cake is done.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with other 1/2 Cool Whip and sprinkle chopped peanuts on top.

title: plain cupcakes
directions: Mix together evaporated milk and water.
Sift flour and measure.
Resift with baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and vanilla thoroughly.
Add sugar and continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with diluted milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Makes 12 dozen.

title: rock's slaw
directions: Shred cabbage finely.
Slice onion thin.
Put layer of cabbage in large bowl (I use Tupperware for this).
Then layer of onion, etc., until bowl is filled.
Pour 2 cups of sugar over this.
Mix together the other ingredients with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture; mix well.
Place in container with tight lid; cover.
Store in refrigerator.
Let stand 4 hours. Stir well and serve.
Keeps as long as it lasts.

title: "easy" meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 8 or 9-inch round casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown beef with onion and salt. Drain fat and stir in beans. Set aside. Combine soup, tomato paste, water, oil, chili powder, garlic and salt. Simmer 15 minutes.
Place 1/2 cup sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
On each tortilla, place 2 tablespoons sauce (smear around) and about 4 tablespoons meat/bean mixture down the center.
Sprinkle 1/8 cup cheese on top of meat/bean mixture and roll up tortilla.
Place flap side down in baking dish.
Fill each tortilla the same until you run out of meat/beans. Pour remaining sauce across the top. Sprinkle on remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with shredded lettuce and sour cream.

title: jaime's meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onions, salt and pepper, egg, oatmeal and tomato sauce in bowl; then place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and mix brown sugar and ketchup.
Spread on top of meat loaf.
Place back in oven for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage, 234° to 238°.
Remove from heat, then blend in remaining ingredients well, then pour into well buttered pan to cool.

title: ham and potato bake
directions: Arrange diced potatoes and ham cubes in a shallow buttered casserole dish.
Stir together the cheese, sour cream, eggs, green onions and seasoned salt.
Pour mixture over ham and potatoes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it looks a little brown.
Sprinkle with green onion slices before serving.
Serves 8 people.

title: mother's rice pudding
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, cook the rice with the water, lime peel and cinnamon stick until softened (about 15 minutes).
Pour off excess water.
Add remaining ingredients and cook at low heat, stirring frequently with a wooden spoon, until the pudding thickens (about 45 minutes).
Transfer to a serving dish; garnish with ground cinnamon.
May be served warm or cold.
Serves eight.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Add meat and let marinate several hours or overnight, turning meat occasionally.
String alternating on long skewers a whole fresh mushroom, cube of beef, squash, onion and green pepper, leaving room on ends for small tomato or large tomato, cubed.
Cook for about 25 minutes, turning often and basting with marinade.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Wash broccoli.
Split broccoli into separate flowerets.
Cut pieces so they are no more than 3 inches long.
Steam broccoli for about 10 minutes.
Remove broccoli and put onto a heated serving dish.
Cover.
Meanwhile, heat olive oil with garlic, remove garlic after 3 to 4 minutes and discard.
Pour hot oil over broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and lemon juice. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Keep hot or serve immediately.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Cut sugar into shortening; combine with flour. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add all liquids and salt to flour mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.
Use as needed.
Yields 5 dozen biscuits.

title: microwave seafood spread
directions: Place cream cheese in a 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave on High for 45 seconds or until soft.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Stir in next 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Spread mixture evenly in pie plate.
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika.
Microwave on Medium-high (70% Power), uncovered, for 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve with crackers.
Yields about 3 cups.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil, water, oil and cocoa.
Pour cocoa mixture into large mixing bowl.
Add flour, sugar, eggs, soda, salt, sour cream and vanilla and beat well.
Pour onto a greased and floured cookie sheet; bake 28 minutes at 375°.

title: country morning julep
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve over finely crushed ice.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pecans evenly on bottom of pan.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts.
Spoon the butter, cheese and sugar mixture over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Don't overbake.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, eggs, milk, soda, salt, corn and drippings. Saute 1 pound ground meat.
Brown and drain.
Pour half the batter on heated greased skillet.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese, meat and onion.
Pour rest of batter on top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: loaf bread
directions: Mix yeast and half of sugar in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add remaining sugar to dry ingredients.
Add yeast and water to dry ingredients with enough
warm water to make good consistency.
Let rise until double.
Knead and divide into 2 loaves.
Let rise. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: microwave easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni, hot water and evaporated milk in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave uncovered on High for 12 minutes or until macaroni is soft and most of liquid has evaporated, stirring twice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until cheese has melted.
Season to taste with minced fresh chives and herbs.
Serves 4.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Lightly beat the egg white with a tablespoon of water.
Dip each chicken cutlet in the mixture, then into the seasoned bread crumbs.
Cover; refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Arrange the cutlets in a nonstick baking dish; drizzle with the melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (turn cutlets over after 15 minutes), or until golden.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked salmon
directions: Let Salmon stand at room temperature for 15 minutes so it is not too cold.
Set the oven at 500.
Lightly butter baking dish. Place Filets in dish and sprinkle with Salt.
Add Milk to almost cover the fish.
Bake uncovered until fish flakes when tested with fork (about 10 minutes) depending on the thickness.
Remove from milk and serve sprinkles with Parsley Flakes and a wedge of Lemon.

title: one dish pork chop meal
directions: Fry chops in very small amount of corn oil until nicely brown. Remove from skillet and drain drippings.
Wipe skillet with paper towel.
Add string beans, potatoes and carrots to skillet. Combine soup mix and water.
Add to skillet.
Top vegetables with chops. Cover and cook on medium-low heat until vegetables are tender.

title: carol's pepper jam appetizer
directions: Both peppers need to be seeded.
Put all of ingredients, except the pectin, into a large kettle and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes; stir constantly.
Remove from heat and pour in the pectin.
Continue to stir until begins to thicken (about 20 minutes).
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 half-pints.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken slowly in hot salad oil.
Remove chicken.
Cook onion and celery in hot oil until tender, but not brown; add remaining ingredients and season.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Place chicken in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; pour sauce over.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: applesauce date bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a shallow baking pan.
Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in dates, nuts and applesauce.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Pour into pan.
Bars should be only 3/4-inch thick when baked.
Bake about 20 minutes or until done.
Cool, cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes at 300°.

title: cheese dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: cran-delight punch
directions: Make ice float ahead of time.
Place ice float in a large punch bowl.
Pour cran-raspberry juice over ice.
Add Sprite. Mix.
Spoon in 1/2 of the raspberry sherbet.
Add remaining sherbet as needed.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix well -- eat and enjoy.

title: cream pie
directions: Place sugar, milk, flour and egg yolks in double boiler.
Cook until thick.
Place into pie shell and cover with meringue made of 2 egg whites beaten stiff with a pinch of salt, 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla folded in.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add pineapple and mix well. Let stand 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Garnish with cherry and pecan halves. Refrigerate until served.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour together.
Add milk, eggs and melted butter; mix well.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake in uncooked crust at 350°.

title: pizza bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll bread dough out on greased pizza pan or cookie sheet. Brush with olive oil. Crush garlic and brush onto oiled dough (I use 2 cloves).
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until puffed and brown. Serve with pizza sauce. Tastes just like Little Caesar's Crazy Bread!

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Alternating milk and flour mixture, mix into egg mixture.
Add flavorings.
Pour into greased pan.
Place in cold oven on middle rack.
Bake at 350° (do not preheat) for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Do not open oven for at least 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cover when cool.
Wait until next day to cut.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in muffin tins or loaf pan at 325° for 25 minutes.
Freezable.

title: shrimp ole
directions: Heat oil.
Add onions, celery and green pepper and cook until tender.
Add flour; cook, stirring constantly, until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, undrained mushrooms, pimientos and seasonings; mix well.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice or corn chips, as desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Combine with salmon, cucumber, lemon juice, mayonnaise, Tabasco and whipped cream.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Turn out onto a platter and garnish with parsley, dill and/or lemon slices.
Serve on crackers or rye bread.

title: cheese dip
directions: Drain pineapple and relish.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in a ball.

title: superfudgy brownies
directions: Mix well flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Stir in sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour mixture, then nuts.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until finger pressed lightly on surface leaves slight indentation. Cool on rack.

title: sauce for beets
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook beets until almost done, then pour sauce over them.
Cook for a little while longer.

title: a very merry cherry dessert
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin (in large bowl) at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water and pie filling.
Refrigerate for 1 hour until slightly thickened.
Place cake cubes in 3-quart serving bowl.
Spoon gelatin mixture over cake.
Refrigerate for 45 minutes until set but not firm.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Stir in 2 cups of whipped topping.
Spoon over gelatin mixture in bowl.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until set. Top with remaining whipped topping.

title: shanghai duck
directions: Place the scallions, star anise and ginger root in a large pot or pan.
Place duck, breast side up.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients and pour over the duck.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer on low heat for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender; turn every hour.
Cut in small pieces and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, then add mix and Jell-O.
Mix well.
Cook 1 hour at 325°.

title: hamburg-sausage dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Then put in a crock-pot with taco sauce and cheese.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Press to pizza pan. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together and spread on top of first mixture.
Place mixed strawberries and glaze on top of cream cheese and sugar mixture. Top with Cool Whip.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish at 350°.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Add the mushrooms the last couple of minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 325° (this is the crust).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender (about 15 to 20 minutes); drain. Add cream of celery soup.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper (optional).
Put in casserole dish.
Lay slices of American cheese on top and bake in moderate oven until cheese is bubbly (10 to 15 minutes).

title: tex-mex tortilla soup
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes; set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine water, beef broth, chicken broth, undrained tomatoes, onion and green pepper and bring to boiling.
Add chicken; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add corn, chili powder, cumin and pepper; cover and simmer for 20 minutes more.
To serve, place crushed tortilla chips into each bowl. Ladle soup over tortilla chips and sprinkle with cheese, avocado and cilantro, if desired.
Serve with lime wedges, if desired.

title: coconut-chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 pies.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift flour and spices together.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately.
Mix well.
Add dates, nuts and jam.
Stir well to distribute evenly. Bake in tube pan that is lined with greased, heavy brown paper or in loaf pans for 1 hour or until cake springs back when you press on it.
Bake at 325° or 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Cream together the sugar and shortening.

Boil together for 3 minutes the raisins and applesauce. Add this to the creamed mixture. Sift together all the dry ingredients and slowly add to the creamed mixture and then add the beaten eggs. Lastly blend in the walnuts. Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean (do not overbake as cake will then be dry).
Cool on rack. Will keep for several weeks.
You may frost if you wish or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over the oleo. Add oatmeal and let steam 20 minutes. Add to oatmeal the sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together and mix in the flour, salt and soda. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut off small tip from wing.
Cut each wing into 2 pieces. Wash and pat dry.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in paper bag. Dredge wings a few at a time, in flour mixture.
Place oil in a heavy skillet to depth of 1-inch.
Heat to 350° and fry wings until golden brown and crisp.
Drain well.

title: tita's spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and cook on very low heat until thickened, about 3 to 4 hours.
If desired, add Tita's Meatballs (above) and cook on low.
Serves an army!
You can freeze half of the sauce and meatballs.

title: celebration punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl; add large mold of ice and serve.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat egg slowly.
Add oil, then sugar and vanilla.
Now add zucchini and pineapple.
In another bowl, measure flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, chopped nuts and raisins.
Add this to wet ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour; test with toothpick.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix in order:
sugar, flour, cocoa, milk, egg yolks and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Let cool slightly and add vanilla.
Pour in prepared crust.
Chill until set.

title: sweet and sour broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower separately until tender.
Drain and place in serving dish; keep warm.
Fry bacon until crisp. Remove and reserve 3 tablespoons of the drippings.
Add onions to drippings and saut for 2 minutes; then stir in brown sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Top with crisp bacon.
Serves 4.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan mix the sugar, milk, marshmallows, butter and salt. Cook stirring constantly over medium heat until it comes to a boil. Cook for 5 minutes at a boil. Do not stop stirring or it will burn. Take off burner. Add chips, vanilla and pecans. Mix well and quickly spread into a buttered 8 or 9 inch square pan. Cool. Cut into 30 pieces.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil until beets are heated through.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off of wings.
Cut wings in half at joint.
Place in pan.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour over wings.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, turning after 1/2 hour.
Brown evenly.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Store in airtight container and use in place of commercially made biscuit mix.

title: applesauce oat muffins
directions: Combine oats, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and soda.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin pan or paper muffin liners placed in muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 18 muffins.

title: hot slaw
directions: Mix all together and bring to boil.
Turn to medium and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Be sure to stir often to avoid sticking.
Will keep in refrigerator to eat fresh for a month.

title: spicy oven fries(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pat potatoes dry.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Toss potatoes is mustard sauce, coating well.
Place on a slightly oiled or sprayed baking sheet in a single layer.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes or until brown and crisp.
Serves 4.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Brown beef in a skillet.
Remove meat from skillet.
Cook macaroni, onion and green pepper in meat fat until onion is soft. Return meat to skillet.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 25 minutes.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco. Add sugar and beat mixture until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well. Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and nuts. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dilled macaroni and chicken salad(low-fat)
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain; rinse in cold water and drain again.
Combine macaroni and chicken in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine milk and remaining ingredients in a small jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over macaroni mixture; toss gently.
Cover; chill 2 hours.

title: dreamy icing
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick.
Cool completely in fridge. Beat sugar, shortening and butter until fluffy on high speed.
Add cooled flour mixture and vanilla; beat until fluffy.

title: posypka(crumb topping for kolace or fruit pie)
directions: Mix well.
Sprinkle on top of kolace or one crust fruit pie before baking.

title: papaya salsa
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to room temperature before serving.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Drain all beans; place in large bowl.
Mix well the following: oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, onion and peppers in a saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over bean mixture; toss well.
Refrigerate until chilled or overnight.
This salad will keep a long time, covered, in refrigerator.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling into greased cake pan.
Dump dry cake mix on top of pie filling.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until thickens.
Pour into browned pie shell and top with meringue from egg whites. Brown in oven until brown.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Stir in beaten eggs. Put cut up rhubarb into pie shell.
Pour mixture over rhubarb. Cover with vented crust and bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in pot until tender (45 minutes to 1 hour). Remove skin and bones.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken in small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hawaiian rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and mushroom pieces in stick of butter.
Add oregano leaves and remove from pan.
Brown rice in same pan (may need to add an extra tablespoon of butter) to keep rice from sticking.
Combine sauteed veggies and rice and place into large casserole.
Pour 1 1/2 cans consomme and 1 can of hot water over rice mixture.
Cook at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Serves 4 to 6 people (I usually double this recipe for 8 people, except for butter).

title: southern sunshine
directions: In pitcher, combine orange juice, ReaLemon juice and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add liquor and carbonated beverage.
Serve over ice.
Makes 7 cups.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: my grandmother's cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly until you have a pastry dough.
Roll or form a 3-inch log and wrap it in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Cut about 2-inch piece of pastry and roll out on floured board.
Cut pastry into about 2-inch squares and fill with cinnamon and sugar, raisins and walnuts.
Roll in a crescent form cookie; place on cookie sheet and brush on some sweet butter on each cookie.
Bake in 400° oven about 12 to 15 minutes.
One batch will yield 60 to 80 cookies.
Serve with powdered sugar.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Put pretzels
and
melted margarine in bottom of baking dish. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole mix soup, milk, pepper, beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until hot.
Stir; sprinkle remaining onions around border of bowl.
Bake 5 minutes (until onions are golden).
Serves 6.

title: deviled ribs
directions: Simmer ribs in about 2 inches of water in covered pan for 1 hour; drain.
Melt butter and add vinegar, ginger ale and seasoning mix in a saucepan.
Brush this mixture over ribs and grill or broil for 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn often and brush with sauce.
Serves 6.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Cover; cool until thickened.
Whip cream until stiff peaks form and fold into cooled pudding.
Add pineapple and oranges; add marshmallows. Cover and chill for 8 to 10 hours.

title: quick ground beef stroganoff
directions: My Grandma's quick noodles.
To be used in chicken or beef soup.

title: helen's festive salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries, cranberry-orange relish and 7-Up.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
Before serving, top with Kraft Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Really easy, really good.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large pretty bowl, layer as directed.
Refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy coconut bundt cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and
1/2 c cream of coconut.
Add eggs, oil and coconut. Bake in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes in bundt pan-greased and floured.

title: glenn's lemon nut cookie
directions: Cream together the first six ingredients.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Form two rolls and wrap in waxed paper. Chill for two hours or longer.
Slice thin and bake at 300° until brown.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and salt to soft ball stage in an iron skillet.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until thick.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix with other ingredients.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes or Pringles and drizzle 1/4 cup melted butter over top; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour into jars and refrigerate.
Keep in refrigerator.
This will keep for many weeks.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, vanilla and butter.
Set aside. Crush the vanilla wafers.
Mix with graham crackers and pecans. Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with crumbs and pour 1/2 of the egg mixture over crumbs.
Add a layer of strawberries (1 cup), then put 1/2 of the Cool Whip on top.
Put rest of crumbs on top, then the rest of the egg mixture on top and rest of strawberries.
Refrigerate for several hours.
When ready to serve, put rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Stir in well beaten eggs. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together. Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and bananas. Add vanilla. Mix well. Pour into lightly greased rectangular pan (9 x 12) and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Cool and frost. Can make 2 round cakes for layer cake.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Boil the water and 1 cup sugar together.
Add the cornstarch, moistened with a little cold water, and cook five minutes.
Then put in the yolks of the eggs, lemon juice, rind and salt.
Cool slightly and pour into a previously baked crust.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: For filling, mix together all ingredients except crust. Pour filling into pie crust. Bake near center of oven at 375° approximately 70 minutes for deep-dish crust, approximately 45 minutes for regular crust.

title: liv's chicken wings
directions: Split chicken wings, tips removed.
Mix equal parts soy sauce, sugar, garlic and juice.
Marinate overnight.
The longer you marinate, the better the flavor.
Place chicken wings with at least half the marinade in roasting pan.
Scrape the sugar syrup from bottom of marinade and pour over chicken.
Bake for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally until brown.
Remove chicken from pan. Reserve juice into saucepan; add some brown sugar to make semi-thick sauce; about 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken when done.

title: never fail cupcakes
directions: Put ingredients in a bowl in order given. Do not mix until last ingredient has been added. Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 22 to 24 cupcakes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Leave fruit in large pieces.
Blend butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and blend.
Mix nuts with 1/4 cup of flour.
Sift the remaining flour and baking powder together.
Add vanilla and blend with butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Pour over nuts and fruit.
Bake in greased tube pan at 250° for 3 hours.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix in	usual way and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put onion-broccoli and soup in skillet.
Mix and heat.
Turn down heat and stir in Cheez Whiz and milk, then add rice.
Put into buttered casserole and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: children's play dough
directions: Heat on stove.
Stir well until thick.
Knead.
Keep in airtight container in refrigerator to keep soft.

title: old fashioned shortcake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, cut in shortening; add milk and egg and mix only to dampen.
Roll out and cut or turn into an 8 inch cake pan and pat to 1 inch thickness.
Brush with melted butter. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush with butter again.

title: meat ball ragout(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Empty soup mix into saucepan. Stir in water. Bring to a boil, stirring often. Cover loosely and cook over low heat 15 minutes.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This mix will keep for 6 weeks in the refrigerator if stored in a covered dish (Rubbermaid plastic container with snap cover.)
Bake in greased muffin pans for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Bake one or more as you need.
Makes up to 50 regular size muffins fresh every morning or meal.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift salt, soda and baking powder with a portion of flour.
Add to creamed mixture with vanilla and sufficient flour to make a soft dough.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and baking powder together; sift again with spices.
Cream oil and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well after each.
Add 1/2 of the flour; beat.
Add 1 1/4 teaspoons water and beat again.
Add rest of flour; beat.
Add rest of water; mix well.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack firmly into pan.
If desired, mold ingredients and place in pan lined with tinfoil.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: joel's spud boats
directions: First find my recipe for Pico de Gallo, putting it together. Okay, now combine the salt, pepper and garlic powder in a small cup.
Set this aside for now.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup of the flour, the sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas, shortening, margarine or butter and milk.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining flour; beat until blended.
Stir in nuts.

title: cheese-less cheesecake
directions: Heat pineapple, sugar and jello until boiling.
Let cool. Whip 1 can evaporated milk with juice from 1 lemon.
Combine with jello mix; put in graham cracker crust.
Chill for several hours.

title: quick lemon butter sauce
directions: Put lemon juice in double boiler and warm, constantly whipping.
Add the butter a little at a time.
Add chopped parsley.
Keep the sauce warm or serve right away.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt white chocolate in large bowl in microwave at low setting.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add a few drops of extract (to taste).
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let harden (may refrigerate).

title: italian chicken
directions: Place washed chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice mushrooms; place on top of chicken along with tomatoes and bay leaves.
Mix Italian dressing with onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with basil and oregano.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°, basting frequently.
Serve with pasta or rice.

title: quick peach melba
directions: Place 1 peach in each dessert glasses.
Spoon out about 1 teaspoon out of each peach cavity.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Pour at once over peaches.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cool until set and top with additional jam or jelly and/or whipped topping.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the chicken, celery, mango, water chestnuts, pineapple, mandarin oranges, mayonnaise, sour cream and coconut extract. Mix together well and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: just plain ol' cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and bake in greased 9 x 11-inch pan for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together well the lime juice, egg yolk and milk.
Drop in food coloring and mix.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Let cool before topping with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: doughnuts (mom's)
directions: Combine beaten egg, sugar and melted Crisco.
Add milk.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and mace.
Combine the liquid and dry ingredients, stirring only until smooth.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thick on floured board or pastry cloth.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter. Fry in Crisco heated to 365°.
(An inch square of bread browns in 60 seconds.)
Turn doughnuts when brown.
Fry until golden brown on both sides (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove.
Drain on paper towels in stand up position.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: cheese whizzers
directions: Cut slices of bread and bacon into thirds.
Spread bread with Cheez Whiz.
Roll up, wrap around bacon and spear shut with a toothpick.
Place on broiling rack and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chow-chow
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers, onions and cabbage; drain.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let set overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to full boil; boil 10 to 15 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and bell pepper.
Mix next 6 ingredients and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix, cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: vermelle's banana split cake
directions: Layer each ingredient in order listed in a large glass dish and place in refrigerator for several hours.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Butter Bundt pan.
Cut bread rolls in half (defrost just enough to cut).
Pour melted butter over rolls, then sprinkle with mixture.
Leave overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix cream cheese, bacon and seasonings.
Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Stuff the caps with cheese mixture and bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in water in large pot until almost done.
Add celery, onion and carrots, then add bouillon, salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 package noodles.
Make sure there is enough water. (Make sure chicken is done.)

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans on a platter.
Mix
the
two
dips together and spread on top of the beans.
Put the
cups	of shredded cheese on next and add the cut
up
tomatoes.
Spread around and put the olive on last.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven 350°. Grease 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan with butter flavor Crisco. Beat

eggs until light and foamy in large bowl of electric mixer. Beat in sugar, vanilla and butter flavor Crisco until creamy. Combine flour with baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture. Mix at low speed until blended. Stir in nuts at low speed. (Mixture will be stiff.) Spread evenly in prepared pan. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until top is light brown. Cool 10-14 minutes. Cut into bars. Makes 2 dozen.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla, then margarine and milk.
Pour into partially baked pie shells.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pecan orange roughy
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray Pam in shallow baking pan.
Place fish fillets in pan.
In small bowl, combine olive oil, lemon juice, paprika, garlic and onion powders, black and white pepper and salt; mix well.
Spoon or brush mixture over the fish.
To the remaining oil mix, add pecans, Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs; mix well.
Spoon mixture over fish evenly.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes one big pie or two small pies.
Very good.

title: crescent pecan pie bars
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Press rectangles to bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of greased pan to form a crust.
Press to seal perforations.
Bake crust at 375° for 5 minutes.
Combine egg, pecans, sugar, corn syrup, melted butter and vanilla in bowl.
Mix and pour over partially baked crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen 4 x 2-inch bars.

title: chicken nugget dipping sauces
directions: For sweet and sour sauce, combine honey and mustard; serve.

title: chocolate igloos
directions: *You need enough to fill 8 dessert shells.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Arrange shrimp in a long dish in a single layer.
Salt and pepper well.
Mix together all the rest of the ingredients before you put on the shrimp.
Pour over shrimp the mixture.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with a salad and French bread.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Dissolve chicken soup supplement in bowl and set aside.
In an oiled wok, stir-fry green pepper, mushrooms, broccoli and green onions.
Set aside.
Oil wok once more, then add chicken and cook until brown, then add Hi-Energy Chicken Supplement mixture, pineapple.
Cook until warm.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder and set aside.
Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and alternate flour and milk.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes (no peeking).

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat yolks of 2 eggs and 1 whole egg.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa and milk.
Boil until thick, stirring all the time.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.

title: baked peas
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs and put in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, sugar and cinnamon.
Add zucchini. Mix together flour, salt, soda and baking powder and add to mixture.
Stir well until blended.
Mix in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 large loaf pans or 3 small pans.
Small pans bake for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until thick.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas (sliced), alternating between wafers and bananas.
Pour thickened mixture over layered wafers and bananas.
Make night before.

title: zucchini snacks(microwave)
directions: Slice zucchini into 3/4-inch slices.
Place in single layer in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes or until slightly softened.
Transfer to paper towels and cool.
Combine all ingredients (except bread crumbs and paprika) in bowl.
Spread on zucchini and dip in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Arrange zucchini slices in a circle on a flat round 10-inch plate.
Microwave (uncovered) on High for 2 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn once during cooking. Repeat with remaining slices.

title: date roll
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until syrup forms soft ball in cold water.
Take off heat.
Stir in dates and pecans.
Roll in damp cloth.
Makes 2 rolls.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
When firm, roll in foil and keep in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix
in a pan sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Put on medium heat and cook until it starts to boil.
(Boil approximately
1 1/2 minutes.) Remove from heat.
Cool for 1 minute. Add
vanilla, salt,
peanut
butter
and oatmeal.
Stir well. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate, marshmallows and milk, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Chill 1 hour or until completely cooled.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into pastry shell.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
If desired, garnish with additional whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix milk and vinegar, set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add milk mixture and yeast.
Stir until thoroughly moistened.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead 1 to 2 minutes. No rising is required.
Store in Ziploc bag in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry onion until transparent, then add Stripples until cooked. Put cubed potatoes and water on medium flame.
As soon as potatoes are tender, but not mushy, add corn, cream and butter.
Leave on heat for 5 minutes.
Don't boil.
Turn heat off and add parsley.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in hot water; add marshmallows while hot, also cream and pineapple.
Let cool, then add mayonnaise, chopped pecans and the whipped cream.
Let cool.
When firm, pour red jello dissolved in 2 cups of water and cooled over the top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Steam broccoli florets. Cook chicken breasts (3 to 4). Add cream of chicken, cream of mushroom and chicken, mayonnaise, lemon juice, sharp Cheddar and melted butter. Add cut, pieced or pulled cooked chicken. Mix all together. Put in casserole dish. Spread Pepperidge Farm seasoning on top, then top with sliced almonds. Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes, then remove cover and brown top.
tags: cream of mushroom and chicken soup

title: soft roll out cookies
directions: Beat egg into milk.
Mix all together.
Roll out and cut in shape desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes about 30 cutouts.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar, salt and cut up marshmallows in boiling water.
Mix until marshmallows are melted.
Add lemon juice and refrigerate until thick.
Add rest.
Serves 8.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Put one cup of pecans in mixture and shape into ball. Roll ball in one cup of pecans. Store in refrigerator.

title: cornbread oyster dressing
directions: In 6-quart kettle, heat 1 cup water and 1 cup butter to melt butter. Remove from heat. Toss with stuffing mix.
Drain oysters. Cut in halves.
In 1/2 cup butter, in medium skillet, saute oysters, onion, green pepper and celery for 5 minutes. Add salt, rosemary and pepper. Add to stuffing.
Toss lightly to mix well. Makes 12 cups, enough for 16 pound turkey.

title: muenster tuna casserole
directions: Melt margarine; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until smooth.
Add milk.
In white sauce, melt cream cheese (cut in cubes).
When smooth, add tuna and olives.
Mix in noodles.
Put 1/3 of mixture in greased casserole.
Top with Muenster cheese, now more tuna noodles and then cheese to layer.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese cocktail biscuits
directions: Blend cheese and butter until light; add remaining ingredients except peanuts.
Knead to form smooth dough.
Pinch off pieces of dough; roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 1 peanut in center of each ball.
Arrange on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be made ahead and refrigerated.
Yield:
36 biscuits.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly; pour into frozen pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot; stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or on high for 3 hours.

title: betty's bourbon balls
directions: Mix Karo syrup and bourbon.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix and form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Let dry overnight and store in tight tin.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add fruit cocktail from can and eggs; mix well.
Pour into two 8-inch cake pans or one large pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Mix by hand.

title: candy creams
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Work in the ground coconut and/or ground almonds.
Add vanilla.
Sweeten to taste.
Roll between 2 sheets of waxed paper or Handi-Wrap.
Make into squares. Refrigerate.

title: layered cheese pate
directions: Combine cream cheese, dried Italian seasoning and pepper in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Line a lightly oiled 6 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with plastic wrap, leaving a 2-inch overhang on each side.
Carefully spread about 1/3 of cream cheese mixture in loaf pan, smoothing to corner of pan.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight or 24 hours. Serves 10 to 12.

title: salsa
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Drain veggies. Do not press veggies.
Add the sugar, brown sugar and white vinegar.
Cook until thick (45 minutes).
Stir often, especially the last 15 or 20 minutes.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients; mix wet ingredients.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Cook over medium heat until mixture leaves side of pan. Remove and knead until smooth.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Slightly beat eggs.
Pull bread apart into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together; let set in refrigerator overnight.
Spoon in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mexican garden salad
directions: Dressing:
Mix 1 cup salsa and sour cream.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil potatoes in water until tender. Pour off any excess water.
Add tomatoes.
Add onion, pepper, celery and carrots.
Cook until veggies are tender.
Add garlic powder, clams and bacon.
Add thyme, basil, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Simmer until flavorful.

title: cherry tomato caper salad
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients. Drizzle over tomatoes, tossing to coat. Let stand at least 15 minutes or up to 1 hour. Sprinkle with basil. Serve over lettuce.

title: saucy potatoes
directions: Stir together and put in crock pot. Cook on medium/low until heated through. Top with cheese if you like. Recipe may be halved for smaller portion.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt.
Mix together salad oil, sugar, eggs, prunes, buttermilk, nuts and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Pour into long flat pan, greased (not floured). Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil whole fryer, salted and peppered, until done.
Remove chicken, but save broth.
Add noodles, onions and celery to boiling water.
When noodles are done, drain but save broth.
Add cheese to hot noodles, then add in both cans of soup and chicken, torn into pieces.
Add enough of the leftover broth to make it creamy, but not thick.
This is quick, easy and delicious.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in microwave for 4 minutes. Take out and stir well.
Return to microwave for 3 minutes more. Add butter and blend well.
Cook 1 minute more until mixture is golden brown.
Add vanilla and baking soda; stir well until foaming.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet and cool.
(Use an extra large measuring cup to cook in.)

title: chex mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients and drizzle with salad oil.
Dump all in a double paper grocery bag.
Shake occasionally for 2 to 4 hours. Kids love to help with this!

title: brunch casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Place bread slices in single layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese and cooked sausage evenly over bread slices.
Mix all other ingredients well and pour carefully over bread, etc. Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: ham-cheese ball
directions: Mix
all ingredients except pecans in a bowl.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Shape
into
ball.
Roll in pecans to coat.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Yields 15 servings.

title: cheese spread
directions: Shred cheeses.
Chop onions and celery.
Combine all ingredients.
Serve with crackers.
Chill a little before serving.

title: broccoli deluxe
directions: Cut up broccoli.
Cook in covered pan in 1-inch boiling salted water until tender 10 to 15 minutes or cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
In saucepan, melt half of the butter or margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; blend in cream cheese until smooth.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix (dry) and jello (dry). Add eggs, oil and 1 small can apricot nectar. Mix well. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Beat 10 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 10 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and beat for 1 minute. Pour into hot, greased skillet. Bake at 450°.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Sift the dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Fold in apples and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: alice's peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt block carefully; do not burn.
Melt slowly.
Add peanut butter; stir.
Add powdered sugar (enough to knead).
Add nuts. Roll into logs or spread in pan.
Cut into slices or squares before it hardens.
Store in airtight bag or containers.
Will keep a long time.

title: elaine's punch
directions: Pour half of each container of juice and 7-Up into punch bowl. Drop half of sherbet by spoonfuls into the liquid.
Stir gently, then serve.
When needed, refill punch bowl with rest of ingredients.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix pumpkin, sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and butterscotch chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix the cream cheese, margarine and vanilla.
Gradually beat in powdered sugar until smooth.

title: tagliarini
directions: Brown meat, salt, pepper, red pepper, oregano, onion, garlic and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 25 minutes.
Add uncooked noodles and cook, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheeses before serving.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and oleo.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and cream of tartar and add to cake.
Add flavoring and coconut.
Stir with a spoon.
Cook in oven (begin in cold oven) for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend soup mix and sour cream thoroughly.
Stir in Italian dressing and shrimp and refrigerate.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt and basil leaves. Pour lemon juice over top. Bake in a preheated 400 degree oven for 40 minutes. Turn chicken over half-way through cooking.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Measure liquids from pineapple and blueberries. Add enough water to make 1 cup and add to gelatin mixture. Stir in blueberries and pineapple. Pour into 2-quart flat Pyrex dish or pan and put in refrigerator until firm.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water and let stand. Combine flour and other dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add 1 cup buttermilk and the yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Mix, then add second cup of buttermilk.
Mix well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs for 3 minutes on medium speed.
Mix dry ingredients and slowly add to egg mixture. Fold in flavoring, apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans (3).
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes or until cake is done.

title: clam spaghetti
directions: Put oil in skillet and add onion and garlic, cooking slowly, about 30 minutes.
Add basil, oregano, salt, pepper and liquid from clams.
Simmer until some of the liquid is reduced.
Cook spaghetti al dente in salted water.
Add clams, parsley and 3 tablespoons cheese to sauce; simmer on low heat for 5 minutes. Drain pasta and add to sauce; stir.
Sprinkle generously with grated cheese and serve from skillet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt
cheese
with milk and stir until smooth.
Fold in broccoli.
Pour
into
casserole, alternating with cheese/milk mixture
and cracker crumbs, ending with cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: zesty french dressing
directions: Blend together in blender and refrigerate.
Makes approximately 1 quart of salad dressing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in cream, flour, sugar, salt and pepper into eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour in 3-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: easy white peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil milk and sugar mixture to soft ball stage.
Stir constantly and let boil for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla into boiled sugar and milk mixture. Beat until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch square greased pan; cool. Cut into squares.
No need to refrigerate.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in greased muffin pan.
Yields 12. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: german tomato salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion and parsley.
Chill.
In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, milk, salt and pepper.
Just before serving, pour mayonnaise mixture over tomatoes.
Top with crumbled bacon. Keeps a short time, but is worth it.
Serves 6 to 8.
Make a double batch!

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream together the margarine, water, salt, sugar and vanilla. Add the flour and nuts and mix well.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Roll in 10x powdered sugar.
Makes around 200 to 220.

title: sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks and sugar until lemon color.
Add cake meal, starch, lemon rind and juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour in ungreased 10-inch angel food pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 1 hour until top is brown.
Turn over onto platter.
Cool completely before removing.

title: chicken-artichoke
directions: Put salt, pepper and paprika on chicken pieces.
Brown them in 4 tablespoons of butter and place in large casserole dish.
Put other 2 tablespoons butter into frying pan and saute mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over chicken and stir in bouillon and sherry in saucepan.
Arrange artichokes around and between chicken.
Pour mushroom/sherry sauce over it and cover.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: foolproof crescent rolls
directions: Add the milk, sugar, eggs, salt, flour and yeast mixture to the melted oleo in the skillet.
No particular order matters.
Mix with a large fork and for ease of mixing, add the flour, one cup at a time, mixing well after each.
Mixture will look thick and may appear to be lumpy.
Okay to use a hand beater for ease of mixing after the third or fourth cup of flour.
Place in a greased bowl (the empty oleo wrappers are perfect for this); cover and put in the icebox overnight.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in half and layer in bottom of pan.
Drain pineapple and spread over Twinkies.
Mix pudding mix by hand and pour over top.
Slice bananas and spread over top of pudding. Spread Cool Whip evenly over bananas.
Chop nuts and sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Chill overnight for best results.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large heavy saucepan until tender. Add cabbage, lima beans, carrots, potatoes, broth and salt.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until carrots and potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Arrange to cover 12 x 5-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat egg; spread over crust.
Bake according to directions on crescent roll package.
Remove from oven.
With back of wooden spoon, pat down so crust won't puff up.
Cool.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with veggies, then cheeses.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: low-fat potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion, celery and carrots in oil. Add cut up potatoes; stir.
Add canned veggie broth.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer until potatoes are cooked.
Add cream at the end of cooking time.
Sprinkle in the dash of dill and parsley.
Serve with rye bread.

title: barbecue sauce(for 10 chickens)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: tennessee barbecue baste
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use as marinade or as basting sauce or table sauce.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add margarine and milk.
Pour in flat pan.
Pour over peaches, juice and all. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until cake is done and slightly browned.
May be served warm with cream or plain. Serves 6.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Cook Jell-O on stove top until gelatin dissolves.
Let Jell-O congeal for about 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients with the Jell-O. Let congeal for 2 hours.

title: walnut-cocoa cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add honey and 2 teaspoons orange peel, beating until light and creamy.
Sift 1/3 cup cocoa and next 5 dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition. Stir in 3/4 cup walnuts.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Turn onto wire racks to cool. Combine 1/4 cup cocoa and butter in mixer bowl.
Add confectioners sugar and cream, beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon orange peel, mixing well.
Spread between layers and over top and sides of cake.
Pat remaining 1/2 cup walnuts around sides.

title: honey-lime dressing
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine honey, lime peel, lime juice and nutmeg.
Beating with an electric mixer on medium speed, add salad oil to honey mixture in a thin, steady stream.
Continue beating until mixture is thick.
Cover and store in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Serve with fruit.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti to package directions; drain.
Stir egg and milk into hot pasta.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add mushrooms, Ragu and seasoning to meat mixture. Spread over noodles.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese last.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Heat the butter and cream
over
medium heat until well heated.
Slowly add 1 cup cheese until it has melted and sauce has thickened.
Toss
fettuccine
with
sauce.
Then
divide evenly between 4 to 6
plates.
Top
each
serving
with extra cheese. Season with pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruits, including the juice (except from cherries). Add instant pudding and toss lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: green onion roll-ups
directions: Clean off onions.
Slice off roots, leaving onion about 6 to 7-inches long.
Separate beef slices, spreading over each some cream cheese.
Place onion on one side of the meat and roll up (may use a toothpick to hold).
Keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, stirring until dissolved. Mix cream cheese with pineapple and nuts.
Fold into cooled jello mixture.
Add whipped cream and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Use of hands improves mixture. Chill.
Roll out into 1-inch balls. (Spray hands with Pam or any nonstick type spray.)
Bake in a 400° oven until golden brown; do not overbake.

title: amish cake
directions: Mix together and pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix milk and bread; let stand a few minutes.
Add eggs, milk and corn.
Put in baking dish and add 1 tablespoon of butter and dash of salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Heat just until sugar melts.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Put 1/2 can of soup on a double piece of foil large enough to wrap around roast.
On top of that, put 1/2 of the package of dried onion soup mix.
Put roast on top and add remaining soup and onion soup on top of roast.
Wrap in foil and place in shallow pan. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour per pound.
Makes a delicious roast and gravy all in one. Also a good way to fix chicken.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Trim veins from cabbage leaves.
Immerse leaves four at a time in boiling water.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or till leaves are limp.
Carefully remove and drain well.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into a large bowl; set aside.
In a 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal into a Glad lock bag with powdered sugar.
