Shake until all pieces are coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: ruby pears
directions: Select pears with good, whole stems.
Peel in vertical strips, from stem to blossom end.
Strain the cranberry sauce through a sieve into a large saucepan or enameled cast-iron casserole (deep).
Stir in remaining ingredients, except peas, to make a syrup.

title: lemon butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Add flavoring and oil.
Cook for least time recommended on box.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together carefully.
Stir in flour. Pat mixture, which may be crumbly, into a greased large cookie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Dough will appear soft, but will be done.)
While hot, sprinkle chocolate chips on top and spread over as they melt.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts (if desired).
Cut into bars or squares when cooled.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Dip in melted chocolate.
Let dry on waxed paper.
Makes 100 pieces.

title: north dakota wheatberry salad
directions: Cook wheat in water until soft (1 to 2 hours).
Drain and cool.
Combine cheese and pudding.
Stir in drained pineapple. Add enough juice only to thicken pudding batter.
Fold in Cool Whip, nuts and wheatberries.
Chill.

title: brownies
directions: Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: italian sausage calzones
directions: Thaw bread dough according to package directions.
Brown Italian sausage in skillet and drain well.
Stir in onion, pizza sauce and mushrooms.
Set aside.
Divide bread dough into 12 equal pieces (or use 12 frozen bread dough rolls).
Pat or roll each piece of dough flat and into a 6-inch circle.
Spoon heaping tablespoonful of meat mixture on each dough circle; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Fold dough over filling and pinch to seal well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes on a well-greased cookie sheet.

title: scotch short bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter and 1/2 of flour until stiff to handle. Place on board and knead in remainder of flour.
Will handle real easily.
Press evenly in long oblong Pyrex dish to bake.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes, then 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown, only slightly on edges.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot. Cut in small squares while slightly brown.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Combine milk and water; add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put 3 cups of cake in bowl.
Add 1/2 cup fruit on that and 1/2 pudding.
Repeat.

title: breakfast or anytime casserole
directions: Place bread in 8-inch square baking dish that has been coated with cooking spray. Layer ham, red pepper and cheese over bread; set aside. Combine milk, eggs, mustard, onion powder and pepper. Pour over cheese and bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours. Remove from refrigerator; let stand 30 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter pecan dessert
directions: Mix.
Spread mixture over last layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: chilli-dilly beans(makes 4 pints)
directions: Combine vinegar and water in pan (not aluminum).
Bring to boiling; keep hot.
In each of 4 hot jars, put 1/2 teaspoon pickling salt, 2 garlic halves, 1 dill head and 1 hot pepper or 1 1/2 teaspoons pepper flakes.
Pack each jar with beans.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Attach lids; process in boiling water bath 5 minutes (10 minutes if elevation is 1001 to 6000 feet).

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Blend brown sugar, soy sauce, ginger, garlic and sesame oil; pour over steak.
Marinate 3 hours; turn occasionally.
Broil or barbecue.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in greased muffin pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans in bowl.
Press over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool. Cream sugar and cream cheese in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Mix in half the whipped topping.
Spread over crust. Combine pudding mixes and milk in mixer bowl; beat until smooth. Spoon over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 15 servings.

title: no cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and 2 cups water.
Mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan and frost with white icing.

title: zucchini and squash bake
directions: Lightly coat baking dish. Place squash and zucchini in a zip and seal bag with the 2 tablespoons dressing. Seal and shake. Add cheese and bread crumbs. Seal and toss lightly. Arrange breaded slices in single layer in pan. Bake at 450° for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container; refrigerate.
Shake before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: kiley's frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Frost cake.

title: chocolate milk pound cake
directions: Soften butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add flour and cocoa.
Mix well.
Pour in chocolate milk, a little at a time. Add vanilla.
Place in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: herbed spinach
directions: Cook bacon bits in large skillet until barely crisp; remove with slotted spoon.
Remove all but 1 tablespoon drippings; to this add onions, spinach, parsley and seasonings.
Cover and cook over medium heat a few minutes (not over 10) until wilted, stirring once or twice.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Cream oleo and crunchy peanut butter together.
Then add 1 pound powdered sugar.
Mix well and add Rice Krispies.
Form into balls, size of walnuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and wax.
Dip balls with toothpick and place on wax paper to cool.
Can be refrigerated for up to 3 months (covered).

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, adding onion, salt, pepper and chili powder.
When browned, add tomatoes and corn.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Pour this into a casserole dish.
In separate bowl, mix corn muffin mix according to directions on box.
Pour this over mixture in casserole dish and bake at 350° until light brown on top, about 45 minutes.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and simmer slowly until flavor is right, probably 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: layered blueberry delight
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with crackers.
Prepare pudding and let stand 5 minutes. Blend in Cool Whip. Spread half of the pudding over the crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and pudding and repeat until all are used.
Top with Cool Whip. Chill for 3 hours.
May use cherries or strawberries.

title: great grandmother bea passmonick's rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, beat together eggs, oil and milk.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Fold in rhubarb.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon topping over batter. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cream soda biscuits
directions: Mix all
ingredients
to form soft dough.
Dust a board with flour.
Roll
to
1/2-inch thick.
Cut into biscuit-sized shapes. Place
in
greased	Dutch oven for 40 minutes with 14 coals on top and 8 on bottom.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter; add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir again.
With wire whisk, blend in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla extract and evaporated milk.
Stir until batter is smooth. Mix in pecans and pour into pie crust.
Bake on preheated baking sheet for 50 minutes or until custard sets.
Remove from oven and allow to cool for at least 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of water, add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Keep at room temperature for 24 hours.
Take out and feed with 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons instant potatoes and 1 cup warm water. Mix well and add to starter.
Let stand at room temperature for 8 to 12 hours (mixture will be bubbly).
Take out 1 cup to make bread and return rest to refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days, then feed again.
If not making bread after feeding starter, throw away 1 cup.
(This is to avoid deflating starter.)

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and chop broccoli.
Add onions and raisins.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture. Crumble fried bacon on top.

title: easy rolls
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar together; set aside.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with chopped nuts.
Cover with chunks of slightly thawed bread dough.
Sprinkle with butterscotch pudding. Pour melted butter and sugar mix over rolls.
Cover with a towel and let set overnight to defrost and rise.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring often. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and cereal. Stir together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with melted chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake
chocolate
cake mix in 2 layers.
When layers are cool, make filling of 30 large marshmallows, one cup sugar, 1 cup
milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook until marshmallows are melted.
Add 14
ounce
can
of
coconut
and
spread filling between
the cooled layers of cake.
Frost cake with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: crab giovanni
directions: Saute onions in olive oil.
Add all ingredients except spaghetti, stir well.
Then add spaghetti.

title: easy meat pie
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add soup and Veg-All.
Season with onion flakes, parsley flakes, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix all well.
Put one of the crusts into a 9-inch pie plate.
Put mixture into the crust and cover with other crust.
Flute the edges.
Cut vent holes in top crust.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: lentil lasagna(serves 12)
directions: Bring washed lentils and water to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes; drain.
Saute onion and garlic in oil. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and cooked lentils. Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.

title: supreme lasagne
directions: Cook 1/2 package lasagne according to directions on package. Brown ground beef with onion.
Add spices, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Layer 1/3 meat sauce, layer lasagne, layer Mozzarella, layer of Ricotta and 2 tablespoons Parmesan in large baking pan.
Repeat, ending with meat sauce and Parmesan.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: vegetarian roast
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Combine remainder of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and place in greased baking dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: simple apple dessert(low calorie recipe)
directions: Peel, core and slice apples; place in baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients and sprinkle over fruit.
Pour Butter Buds over all.
Microwave 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes on High.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender.
Serve cold or warm.
One half cup contains 60 calories.

title: cheesy ham and potato casserole
directions: In a medium pan, heat cheese and cream, stirring constantly until cheese is melted and sauce is creamy.
Remove from heat and stir in potatoes, ham and pimento.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: new potatoes and peas
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, place potatoes.
Add water to cover potatoes. Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium. Cook 8 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Drain in colander.

title: dilly salmon pie
directions: Sprinkle half the cheese in the pastry shell.
Remove any bones and skin from salmon; break into chunks.
Mix lightly with flour and put into shell.
In a pan, heat butter; saute onion until soft.
Add soup, sour cream, dill and pepper.
Heat and stir until it boils.
Remove from heat.
Mix in eggs; pour over salmon. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until set.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix and freeze.
Take out 30 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions and then place in crock-pot. Add all remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Heat on high for 3 hours or on low most of the day.

title: grandma's bake bananas
directions: Peel banana (better to use firm bananas).
Split the long way and place in a greased baking dish or flat pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and baste with melted butter.
Bake in a hot oven until brown.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Mix together; put in a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° to 375° until top forms a crust.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Boil sweet potatoes for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients in with sweet potatoes after boiling them.
Spread in a square baking pan.
Let bake for about 30 minutes.
Makes 12 or more servings.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into hot, oiled muffin tins.
Bake at 450° until done.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: vanilla wafer delight
directions: Take mixing bowl, miniature marshmallows and bag of Hershey's chocolate chips, then take Hershey's chocolate chips and mini marshmallows and heat in microwave for 1 minute or until melted. Then about 30 seconds through the minute, mix up the bowl; keep doing this until completely melted.
When done in microwave, let bowl sit for 2 minutes.
After bowl has set, relax and dip your vanilla wafers in the rich and delightful tasting chocolate and marshmallow mix.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/4 cup water and salt until barely tender; drain.
Arrange in greased 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix soup with evaporated milk and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with onion rings.
Return to oven and bake until onion rings are crisp and brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar, stir and let stand overnight. Add Dream Whip, marshmallows and nuts, if desired, when ready to serve.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into small wedges and place in greased casserole dish. Brown and drain hamburger and onion; mix with rice and pour over cabbage. Chop or mash tomatoes and pour over top. Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tomato cheese tart
directions: Prepare pie crust mix following label directions, adding 1/2 cup of the Cheddar cheese.
Roll out or flatten and push into pie plate bottom and up the sides.
Prick with fork, sides and bottom. Bake in hot oven, 425°, for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Spoon remaining Cheddar and Swiss cheeses into pie crust.
Slice the tomatoes into thin wedges.
Arrange, slightly overlapping in an attractive pattern over the cheese.
Sprinkle with spices and sauteed onions over top, then sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes until tomatoes are tender.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix together; put into the crock-pot for 24 hours on low heat.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs on a jelly roll pan.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 450° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Drain off any fat. In a saucepan, combine all remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over ribs.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake uncovered for 1 hour, basting frequently.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: harvest cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine apples with sugar.
Let stand 1 hour. In another bowl, mix the flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. In a large bowl, combine eggs, oil and vanilla.
Using a beater, mix until well blended.
Add apples, a little at a time, alternating with flour mixture.

Blend mixture well. Add walnuts. Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours until done. Cool in pan for 25 minutes, then turn out onto a serving plate. Dust top with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: pralines
directions: Mix whipping cream and brown sugar together.
Microwave for 15 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Mix butter, pecans and vanilla. Drop onto buttered foil.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add
onion and green pepper. Cook together for 15 minutes, mixing thoroughly.
Add tomatoes (break them up), kidney beans,
tomato sauce and chili powder. Mix thoroughly.
Cover pot and
simmer
minutes
stirring occasionally.

title: special green beans
directions: Wash beans, trim ends and remove strings.
Combine beans and water in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp to tender.
Drain.
Plunge beans in ice water to stop cooking process.
Drain and set aside.
Saute mushrooms and next 7 ingredients in oil in Dutch oven.
Stir in beans and cook until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix onion,
soup,
egg and mayonnaise together and pour over broccoli.
Mix butter and toss in stuffing.
Put dressing mix on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheddar zucchini supreme
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter, then add next 5 ingredients. Heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add half the cheese, heating and stirring until cheese is melted.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese and bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine meat, salt, water, bread crumbs and egg.
Mix well. Shape into balls.
Set aside.

title: sherried fruit
directions: Heat butter, sugar, flour and sherry.
Pour over fruit and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Butter bottom of pan.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift flour and soda.
Combine orange slice candy, dates, nuts and coconut.
Add 1/2 cup flour; stir well.
Cream butter; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs to creamed mixture, one at a time. Add soda to buttermilk.
Alternately add milk and flour, beating well after each addition.
Add candy mixture.
Put in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: speedy chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add all other ingredients in large stew pot and warm to your liking.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix margarine, sugar,
flour and coconut by hand.
Take out 2 cups for topping.
Add
egg and vanilla.
Pat in pan and add filling;
then sprinkle
on
topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with veggies.

title: country kitchen casserole
directions: Arrange cooked vegetable and eggs in a shallow pan (1-quart baking dish).
Stir soup until smooth and gradually add milk. Pour over vegetable and eggs.
In a bowl, combine butter and water and stir in dressing mix.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: warm jasmine rice salad
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together the apple juice, honey, cornstarch and if desired, ginger, until the cornstarch dissolves. Add the blueberries, then bring to a simmer over moderate heat; cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Remove from the heat and stir in the lime juice.
Serve hot or warm.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies will be soft.
They will puff during baking and flatten during cooling.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half (lengthwise).
Place cream side up in a 13
x
9-inch
cake pan, then mix pudding and milk until thick. Pour on top of Twinkies, then top with Cool Whip.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak pickles and onions in salt water 3 hours and then drain. (Use the 1 cup salt and water.)
Make pickling mixture from the first six ingredients and pour over pickles and onion.
Cook, bringing to boiling point.
Pack in clean, hot jars and seal.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: You also need a
9x13 greased pan and double boiler.

title: cashew nuts shrimp
directions: Shell and clean the shrimp. Rub the shrimp with salt and rinse.
After it dries, marinate with 1/4 tablespoon salt, 1/4 tablespoon cornstarch, sesame oil and a dash of pepper for 15 minutes. Add shrimp to 4 cups boiling water.
Fast boil until cooked and put them aside.
Heat 5 cups oil in pan. Fry cashew nuts for 1 minute. Put aside.
Use same pan and oil; quickly fry the shrimp.
Put them aside. Drain the excess oil from the pan. Stir-fry the carrots, ginger, scallions and green peas quickly. Add cooking wine. Add shrimp.
Mix 3/4 tablespoon cornstarch with 1/4 tablespoon salt, sesame oil and 3 tablespoons water in a bowl. Pour them into the pan and stir-fry.
Add in cashew nuts. Stir-fry quickly and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Combine eggs, sugar, oil, water and pumpkin. Add remaining "dry" ingredients. Mix well. Divide batter between 2 pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add pizza sauce to beef.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Spread noodles on bottom of cake pan. Spread hamburger and sauce over noodles.
Add mushrooms, olives, pepperoni and other desired toppings.
Then spread cheese over the top.
Bake about 20 minutes at 250°.

title: maryann's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add walnuts or pecans.
Press firmly in an even layer over bottom of 6 1/4 x 10 x 1 1/4-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Prick the eggplant several times and microwave, uncovered, until collapsed and soft (10 minutes). Set it aside to cool. Spread walnut pieces on a microwave-safe dish and cook, uncovered, until fragrant and toasted (2 to 3 minutes). Chop fine. Scrape the eggplant flesh into a bowl and chop coarsely. Add walnuts, onions, parsley, pepper, garlic, salt and pepper. Combine. Stir in oil and lemon juice. Cover and let stand at room temperature for several hours.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix the cheese and butter well. Blend flour and red pepper. Then add Rice Krispies.
Let chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: barbecue brisket--in the oven
directions: Spray a large roasting pan with Pam.
Wash brisket.
Massage liquid smoke on both sides of brisket.
Massage barbecue sauce on both sides of brisket.
Place meat with fat side up and seal top of pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for approximately 4 1/2 hours. Check to see if tender or needs a little more time.

title: chicken and dumplings(by edna bell)
directions: Simmer	chicken
in 2 quarts water until tender.
Cool; set broth aside.
Remove chicken bones.
Cut chicken into bite sizes pieces.

title: 7-minute icing
directions: Prepare double boiler for boiling.
Prepare electric mixer for mixing.
Prepare pan of ice water for cooling.

title: molasses spice cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Add shortening and cream.
Add molasses and eggs.
Mix and drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Be careful when baking to take out before completely done.
Let stand on sheet for 2 minutes and they are easier to remove.
Makes 100 cookies. Batter is very stiff; cookies crisp and chewy.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Cook pudding by instructions and pour into crust.
Put in fridge until set.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep in fridge until ready to eat.

title: bread bowl dip
directions: Cut center out of round loaf.
Mix soup mix with sour cream. Chill for about 2 hours.
Cut center of round loaf and Italian bread into cubes.
Spoon sour cream mixture into hollowed out bread.
Place bread cubes and veggies around bread and dip.
Enjoy. A real crowd pleaser!

title: glazed pecan carrots
directions: In large dry skillet over medium-high heat, toast pecans for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring frequently; set nuts aside.
In same skillet over medium heat melt butter.
Add carrots; cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients, except pecans and cornstarch.
Cook covered, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 12 minutes, or until carrots are tender. Transfer 2 tablespoons liquid from skillet to small dish; stir in cornstarch until dissolved.
Stir cornstarch mixture into carrots; cook an additional 2 minutes or until sauce is thickened and carrots are glazed.
Stir in pecans.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cajun-country bread pudding with rum sauce and soft cream
directions: Pour 7 tablespoons butter or margarine into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Swirl around to coat bottom and sides.
Pour excess butter or magarine and additional 1/4 cup butter or margarine into a small bowl; set aside.
Place bread crumbs in buttered baking dish; set aside.

title: vermicelli
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain fat.
Brown fideo lightly.
Mix beef, fideo, soup and 1 soup can of water.
Cover and simmer until fideo is tender.
Season to taste with chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper.

title: potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with salt.
Combine soup, cream cheese, ham and milk.
Heat over low heat until blended.
Pour over potatoes. Pour into baking dish.
Top with sliced or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: flounder in zucchini sauce
directions: Sprinkle fillets lightly with salt.
Roll up loosely like small jelly rolls.
In large skillet, heat margarine; cook onion until tender.
Stir in zucchini, tomatoes, basil and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Arrange fish rolls in zucchini mixture.
Cover; cook 8 to 10 minutes until fish flakes.
Baste occasionally.
Sprinkle with lemon peel.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: lumpiang shanghai
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly, except wrappers and oil. Divide into 10 parts.
Wrap each part in a lumpia wrapper, making a long thin cylinder.
Moisten ends with water to seal.
Fry 3 to 4 pieces at a time in medium-hot oil for about 6 to 8 minutes, rolling each piece to brown all sides evenly.
Drain on paper towels.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Serve hot with sweet sour sauce.

title: springy summer salad
directions: Blanch broccoli and cauliflower in a colander by first pouring boiling water over vegetables, then ice cold water.
Combine with all remaining ingredients, including enough salad dressing to coat mixture.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: talarina
directions: Cook oleo, onion, salt, bell pepper and ground beef until tender.
Add soups, corn, olives and noodles and cheese.
Mix together and pour in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven or until cheese melts.

title: ham and red eye gravy
directions: In frying pan, put the ham.
Cover with water and bring to a boil to remove excess salt.
Drain off water and add the lard. Fry gently until done, not hard.
Remove ham to a shallow bowl. Add a little water to pan, stirring any brown that stuck to pan. Add coffee.
Pour over ham in dish and pass around table to be spooned over rice, grits or a split biscuit.

title: creole black-eyed peas
directions: Cook bacon in
a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.

Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in drippings until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients and cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf and sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serves 6.

title: easy double chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup chocolate morsels and butter, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda, eggs, and vanilla.
Stir with wooden spoon until blended. Add 1/2 cup morsels and nuts.
Spread batter in prepared pan. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup chocolate morsels.
Bakes 25 to 30 minutes just until set.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Makes 2 dozen.

title: rice and black bean salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Whisk together the oil and lime juice in a small bowl.
Pour over rice mixture and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
Yields 6 servings.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead, cover and refrigerate.)

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In a 1 3/4-quart shallow microproof casserole, combine potatoes, soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese.
Blend well.
tags: frozen Southern style hashed brown potatoes

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla carefully.
Fold in sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Grease and flour a tube pan (not Bundt).
Pour half of batter in pan and use half of topping.
Use rest of batter and topping.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed for 15 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 60 to 65 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.
For better slicing, refrigerate bread overnight.

title: italian jonets
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Make a well in center and pour in oil, milk, egg and extracts.
Mix well to make a medium firm dough.
If too sticky, add a bit more flour.

title: mom's cornbread
directions: The thinner the consistency, the lighter the bread.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Cook rice according to directions on box.
In a large bowl, combine sausage, rice, milk, soup and 1 1/2 packages of cheese.
Pour in casserole dish. Top with remaining cheese. Cook for 10 minutes or until the cheese is bubbly at 350°.

title: quick and easy buns
directions: Melt oleo in oven.
Add all ingredients except biscuits; mix well.
Place biscuits in syrup in 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each egg is added.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add this alternately with milk.
Add the vanilla and lemon flavoring last.
Bake in large tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: oven chicken and linguine
directions: Melt butter in a 10 x 15-inch baking dish in a 400° oven, then remove dish from oven.
Stir onion, garlic, basil and pepper into butter.
Place chicken in butter mixture, then turn over to coat. Bake, uncovered, until meat is no longer pink when slashed (about 45 minutes).

title: date loaf
directions: Whip cream until stiff.
Clip marshmallows and mix.
Cut nuts and dates and crumble crackers and mix all together.
Save enough crackers to roll log type loaves in.
Roll loaves in crackers and wrap in foil.
Chill.
Slice to serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Break Reese's cups into pieces and scatter on crust.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating until creamy.
Add sour cream.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into buttered and floured Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Inserted toothpick will come out clean.

title: 7-up party salad
directions: Combine
7-Up
and
marshmallows in saucepan; cook over medium heat
until
marshmallows are melted.
Add lime jello, stirring until dissolved.
(Have cream cheese at room temperature.) Add the
hot
mixture
to cream cheese;
beat in mixer until
smooth. Add
pineapple and walnuts; chill until partly set.
Fold
in whipped cream and mayonnaise. Blend thoroughly. Pour into a very lightly oiled 2 quart size mold.
Refrigerate until
firm. Loosen
edges
and	invert	on
serving
plate. Garnish with sugar frosted grapes and slices of pineapple.
I put it in 2 pans. It keeps for days in refrigerator.

title: red cabbage
directions: Saute chopped onion in a little fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until the cabbage is done.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients. Roll in small balls and press down with glass dipped in colored sugar. Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: annual 4th of july flag cake
directions: *Use some for whip layer.
Save about 40 slices for the flag.

title: waffles
directions: Separate egg and beat egg white until stiff.
Mix flour, egg yolk, sugar, buttermilk, and oil with beater.
Gently fold in egg white with a spoon.
Spread thin layer of batter in waffle iron and bake.
Makes about 1 serving.

title: tomato aspic
directions: In a clear glass bowl, add 2 cups boiling V-8 juice to jello. Stir until dissolved.
Add 2 cups of cold V-8 and stir.
Let set in refrigerator until cool.
Add onions, celery, olives and shrimp. Place in refrigerator until set up.
Place dollop of mayo in center of set up aspic and sprinkle with paprika and pinch of parsley.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients well.

title: georgia's goulash
directions: Fry ground meat in pressure cooker.
(Use salt to keep from sticking.)
Add onion and keep stirring until meat shows no pink. Do not brown.
Add macaroni, tomatoes, water and seasoning.
Bring to pressure and cook 5 minutes.
Let gauge return to normal. Open and serve immediately with shredded cheese topping each serving, or if served family style on top of bowl.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except Sprite.
When you put punch in bowl, add about 1/3 of the Sprite.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: chicken pepper skillet
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half; remove skin and bones.
Cut chicken into 1/4-inch thick strips.
In medium bowl, mix chicken, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, garlic and sugar.
Set aside.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except sour cream.
Put half in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Put the sour cream over the mixture, then put the rest of the mixture on top.

title: chicken bologna
directions: Add Tender
Quick
to meat.
Grind twice and let set 24 hours, then add the
black
pepper, brown sugar, saltpetre and liquid smoke.
Grind again and
mix
well.
Put
in
cans	and process 1 hour at 10 pounds pressure.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Combine egg and milk into a bowl large enough for dipping chops into.
Dip each chop into the mixture, then roll in the corn flakes.
Place chops on a semi-flat baking pan and salt to taste. Place a pat of butter on each chop and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours, turning once.
Less baking time is needed for thinner chops.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour cake pan. Cream together butter. Crisco and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Sear the chops in a small amount of oil.
Add uncooked rice, tomatoes, onion, etc.
Turn heat to low, cover with a heavy lid and cook about 45 minutes.
Lift pork chops from pan, with spatula, including rice and onions.
Serve with garnish.

title: confederate deep fried turkey
directions: May substitute cayenne pepper for red pepper.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Slice potatoes, carrots, onions and celery. Arrange vegetables in a casserole.
Add a layer of pork chops.
Top with vegetables.
Make a gravy of the butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk, cooking until slightly thickened.
Pour over the vegetables and pork chops.
Bake 45 minutes to 60 minutes at 350°. Cover during first half of cook time, then remove lid to finish cooking.
Carrots and onions may be omitted.

title: a quick lunch
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in boiler and start cooking on medium-heat.
Take the can of Hormel roast beef and chop up.
Add sage and pinch of red pepper.
Add to ingredients in boiler and cook on medium-heat about 30 minutes or until tender.

title: cheese and beef dip
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms.
Brown ground beef.
Cook Ro-Tel or Old El Paso sauce until it thickens a little bit; then cut up cheese and add.
When cheese is melted, add onion and mushroom mixture.
Drain ground beef and add.
Mix well and serve.

title: beef stew
directions: In a plastic bag, combine flour and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Add meat cubes a few at a time, shaking to coat.
In a large saucepan, add onion and thyme.
Stir in vegetable juice, bouillon, pepper sauce, potatoes, carrots and 1 cup of water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Skim off fat.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly blend cream cheese and Cheddar cheese with onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in pineapple.
Chill several hours; then shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Turn back temperature to 350° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: wild and cheesy chicken
directions: In a large skillet, melt oleo and saute onions, celery and green peppers.
Add cream of mushroom soup, milk and chicken. Blend together well.
Prepare wild rice according to package.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in mushrooms and cheese.
Pour mixture into a casserole and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Combine margarine, cooking oil, cocoa and water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix together the buttermilk, eggs, cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Pour into other mixture.
Put into greased, floured 10 x 15-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey balls
directions: Cream butter and honey.
Stir in flour, vanilla, nuts and salt.
Chill.
Roll into balls.
Cook at 300° for 40 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar after removed from oven.
Roll again in sugar after they are cold.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Heat soups
together and pour over chicken in casserole. Alternate soup and chicken.
Prepare the package of Pepperidge Farm dressing as directed on
package
for
dry
crumbly
recipe. Pour
over chicken mixture and bake in
oven at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until heated thoroughly.
If
using
large casserole, increase amount of chicken and mushroom soup.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together zucchini, onion, sour cream and cream of chicken soup.

In separate bowl, mix stuffing with 1/2 cup melted butter. Put half of this mixture in bottom of casserole pan; pour zucchini mixture in next, then top off with other half of stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream the butter and shortening, then sugars.
Stir in eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture. Add oats.
Mix well, adding cereal, coconut and pecans. Drop large spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: In deep fat fryer, heat oil to 350°.
In shallow bowl, combine egg, milk, Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce and 1 tablespoon flour.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
In another bowl, combine remaining 2 cups flour with salt and pepper to taste.
Dip pickle slices first into egg mixture and then into flour.
Dip egg a second time and into flour again, two full turns each.
Fry pickles until golden brown, drain on paper towels.
Serve hot. Yield: 4 servings.

title: cap'n crunch clusters
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and melt candy in microwave dish in microwave for 3 minutes and then 2 minutes.
Stir and pour over mixture, then spoon out on wax paper.
Let set before removing.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease dish and fill 2/3 full of sliced apples.
Blend first 5 ingredients together and pour on top of apples.
Pour melted butter over top of mixture on apples.
Add cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yummy meatballs
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients in large bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Arrange in rows in casserole.
Blend remaining ingredients in bowl.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen lemon dessert
directions: In large bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating until egg whites are a thick, shiny meringue.
In a medium bowl, beat yolks until light colored and thick.
Beat in lemon rind and juice.
Fold egg yolk-lemon mixture into egg whites.
Beat cream in chilled bowl until it holds its shape. Fold cream into egg white mixture.
Sprinkle half of the crumbs in the bottom of a buttered 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour in lemon mixture; lightly smooth with spatula.
Sprinkle surface with remaining crumbs.
Put in freezer overnight (if longer, cover with aluminum foil).
To serve, cut in squares. Serves 12.

title: chocolate pecan torte
directions: Roll prepared pie dough to fit an 11 inch torte pan.
Cut away any excess dough.
Set aside.
In 2 quart bowl, cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla, mix well.
Place chips and nuts in bottom of torte pan.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Bake at 300° on middle or lower oven rack for 45 minutes or until firm in center.
Cool completely before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions with salt; mash together and drain all water.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and pimentos; add to squash.
Melt oleo or butter; stir in herb crumbs.
Line bottom of casserole dish with crumb mixture.
Pour squash mixture on this; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tortellini salad *
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Microwave or steam broccoli and carrots, slightly, but don't cook through.
This wasn't in the original recipe, but I think the vegetables absorb more flavor this way.)
In large mixing bowl, combine cooked tortellini, sweet pepper, broccoli, carrot and olives.

title: dill rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix together.
Let rise 1 hour; shape into balls.
Let rise.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Lightly grease pans.

title: international coffee
directions: Mix together.
Stir in hot water to taste.

title: dough for fried pies
directions: Make dough and cover in Tupperware to chill.
This will keep in refrigerator at least 2 weeks.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Cut up sausage or bacon, place in Dutch oven and cook on medium heat for a few minutes.
Cut up cabbage; place on top of meat; salting each layer.
Add half cup of water to the cabbage; put lid on.
Cook on medium heat for 25 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Put marshmallows and hot milk in bowl and let stand.
Mix all together and press in pan lined with wax paper.
Chill for 2 days before serving.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Freeze bread slices; cut off crust, then break into cubes and cover bottom of buttered Pyrex dish.
Cover bread cubes with sausage.
Mix eggs, dry mustard, salt and milk.
Pour over sausage.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. (Can be prepared the night before and kept in refrigerator.
Bake next morning.)

title: cracker crunch chicken
directions: Crush crackers.
Add all ingredients, except butter.
Dip chicken in butter, then crackers mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Good with fish or pork chops, also.)

title: grandma's angel biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Knead dough until smooth.
Roll and cut as desired.
Bake on middle rack of preheated oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Dough can be covered and refrigerated for a week, using as needed.

title: rice stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook onion, garlic powder and chili powder in butter or oleo until tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except mushroom caps.
Form into 24 small balls.
Remove stems, wash and dry mushrooms.
Place mushroom caps on rack in broiler pan, rounded side up.
Brush with melted butter and broil 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn mushroom caps; season with salt and pepper.
Place ball of rice mixture in each cavity.
Drizzle with melted butter and broil until golden brown.
Makes 24 mushrooms.

title: chip dip
directions: Put block of cream cheese in bowl and pour salsa over cream cheese.
(Pour enough salsa so it will cover cream cheese.)

title: double fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs. Stir in nuts.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until center is set.

title: barley meal
directions: In 5-quart saucepan, heat canned beef, chopped onion, salt and sliced carrots.
Add 2 quarts water, barley and rice.
Cook until barley is soft and water is absorbed.
Sometimes more water is needed.
Add peas, broccoli, mushrooms and mushroom soup; simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 12 people.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in cubes.
Boil with 1 teaspoon salt and onion, covered, for about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Make layers of eggplant, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and crackers.
Pour in milk; dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: spiced cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in cranberries, orange, apple, walnuts, cinnamon and cloves.
Chill until set.
Pour into a 4 cup ring mold.
To serve, unmold onto a serving dish.
Garnish as desired.

title: harvest popcorn mix
directions: Place dried apple in a large bowl.
Combine honey and pumpkin pie spice.
Pour over dried apple, tossing gently to coat.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add soups and chilies; add sour cream and chicken and season to taste.
Heat for a few minutes.
Crush Doritos slightly.
Put layer of crushed chips on bottom of casserole, then layer of chicken mixture, then cheeses.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: mushroom-barley-beef soup
directions: Place barley in saucepan.
Cover with water; let it come to a boil.
Cover pot and let it simmer until all water is absorbed. Cut meat into very small cubes.
Add to chicken broth and bouillon cubes.
Let cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, celery, onion and mushrooms.
Cook for 1 more hour.
Add barley, salt and pepper to taste.

title: cabbage-onion salad
directions: Alternate cabbage and onions in a bowl, with onions for top layer.
Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add salad oil.
Drip the hot mixture over cabbage and onions; do not stir.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or longer before serving.

title: chicken fried hamburger
directions: Shape hamburger into patties; chill.
Place milk and flour in a flat dish.
Place each patty in milk; turn over, then dip in flour.
Place patties in hot skillet with melted shortening. Season.
Cook on each side until crispy, flattening as they cool.

title: iron skillet rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast, salt, sugar and oil.
Add 2 double handfuls of flour; mix.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into rolls; put in iron skillet (oiled).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix cookies and melted butter together.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Spread ice cream over cookies and press peanuts into ice cream.
Freeze.
Soft boil milk, butter, chocolate chips and powdered sugar
for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla. Cool to room temperature.
Pour on top of peanuts.
Put cool whip on top.
Freeze until firm.

title: gingersnaps(cookies)
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into molasses mixture.
Form in small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar; place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about ten minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice tomatoes; cover with salt and hot water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Rinse tomatoes well; add lemon, cinnamon, nutmeg and tapioca.
Mix well, put in pie shell and dot with butter.
Put on top crust and slit 4 or 5 times for venting. Bake for 45 minutes to an hour.
Watch pie crust carefully, it might not take quite this long to bake it.

title: macaroni deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni about 10 minutes.
Stir in broccoli.
Drain both.
In same pot, melt oleo, cheese, milk and soup until blended.
Stir in drained macaroni and broccoli. Add meat.
Place mixture in casserole dish.
Can be frozen until needed or bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: swordfish skewers
directions: Remove the skin from the swordfish and cut into 1 1/2 to 2-inch cubes.
Cut peppers into 2-inch squares.
Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch sections, discarding seeds and letting any juice run off. Slice lemons into 1/4-inch thick disks and then into half moon shapes.

title: sunshine loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; cut off top of pumpernickel loaf and take out all of the center to make it into a bowl. Fill with mixed ingredients and cover (shiny side in) with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nana's easy poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan that has been coated with sugar.
(You can also use 2 medium bread pans or 3 small ones:
one to eat, one to freeze and one to give away.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan(s) immediately.

title: melt away cookies
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together.
Cream together with butter. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not brown.
Top with:

title: spicy almond chick
directions: Melt butter; add chicken and lightly brown.
Place chick in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet.
Cook until jelly is dissolved.
Pour mix over chick.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together. Quarter biscuits and cover thoroughly with cinnamon/sugar mixture. (A zipper plastic bag works well for this.) Melt butter and add remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture. Place half of biscuits into tube pan and cover with half of butter/cinnamon/sugar mixture. Add second half of biscuits and cover with remaining melted butter mixture. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Invert pan onto a plate 5 minutes after removing from oven. Serve hot. Pulls apart with fingers.

title: strawberry ?  ?  ?  ?
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: mock spiced apple rings(relish)
directions: Use large cucumbers or zucchini that will fit through neck of canning jars after sliced.
(I use wide mouth jars.) Peel, slice 3/8-inch thick and remove seed centers to make rings.
Mix lime to 4 1/2 quarts water.
Pour over veggie rings; soak for 24 hours. Rinse well and soak in clear water for 3 hours.
Then drain.
Mix 1/2 cup vinegar, alum and red food coloring.
Add this with enough water to cover.
Simmer 2 hours.
Drain well.

title: shortcake
directions: Use 13-inch square baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into serving squares.
Top with fresh fruit.
Serves 12.

title: butterscotch pecan patties
directions: Mix white sugar, brown sugar, syrup and salt and cream together.
Cook to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking over simmer same burner, stirring occasionally to 238° or until few drops form a soft ball when dropped into cold water. Remove from heat.
Add butter; cool at temperature without stirring until lukewarm or until the hand can be held on bottom of pan.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until candy will hold its shape.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Place in large baking dish.
For your cheese sauce, melt 1 stick margarine in saucepan.
Add flour; mix until smooth.
Add milk.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add diced Velveeta cheese; cook until melted.
Pour over cauliflower. Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake in hot oven until slightly browned.

title: zucchini stuffed with ham and pasta
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise in half; using spoon, scoop out centers, leaving shells about 1/4-inch thick.
Place shells in boiling water.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, for 7 minutes or until almost tender.
Place upside down on paper towels to drain thoroughly.
In large saucepan over high heat, bring 2 quarts water to boil.
Add pasta; cook 9 minutes, stirring frequently, until almost tender.

title: sauerkraut and spareribs
directions: In a large roaster or baking dish, put spareribs.
Take sauerkraut, put on top of spareribs.
Cut up potatoes and put in roaster.
Add onions.
Add parsley, basil, dill, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken packets
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Unroll the crescent rolls and press each pair into a rectangle.
Place 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of chicken mixture into the center of each rectangle. Fold dough over and seal edges tightly.
Roll each packet in melted butter and then in croutons or cracker crumbs. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 packets.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs, then blend in other ingredients except marshmallows. Grease and flour oblong pan and cook 30 minutes on 300°.
Remove and spread marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until marshmallows melt.
(Watch closely.)

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef; mix in taco sauce and taco mix and set aside.
Mix all else except lettuce, meat and Doritos.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add beef, lettuce and Doritos.

title: hardtack candy
directions: Place sugar, Karo syrup and water in a heavy pan.
Cook until mixture reaches 300° on candy thermometer.
Stir in oil and food coloring.
Pour into jelly roll pan.
Let cool.
Break into bite size pieces.
For peanut butter flavored candy, add 2 tablespoons smooth peanut butter.
You do not need to add food coloring with peanut butter.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream Sucanat (or brown sugar) and butter.
Add eggs and beat. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: lynda's "blue ribbon" corn bread
directions: Place crumbled cornbread and bread in large bowl and sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Pour approximately 2 to 2 1/2 cups hot broth over this mixture.
Let stand about 30 minutes or until you can "smush" it between your fingers.
Saute chopped onions and celery in 1/2 cup broth until soft.
Add this to cornbread mixture.
Break eggs and beat, one at a time, and add to mixture.
Add remaining broth and mustard.
Beat well with spoon or fork.
Dressing should be fairly thin.
If too dry, you might add a little water or broth.
Place in baking dish and bake at 300° to 325° for about an hour.
Check at about 45 minutes and if it is getting too dry, you might cover it loosely with aluminum foil for the remainder of cooking time.
Serve with Giblet Gravy.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Beat chicken breasts with meat mallet.
Place a slice of ham on top of chicken and then a slice of cheese on top of ham.
Roll up as tight as possible and roll in flour.
Fry in margarine until brown on each side.
May have to fasten with a toothpick.
Next, place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle mushrooms around on top. Mix soups together and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Chop onion and parsley.
Cut pepper into 1/8-inch slices.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium high heat until hot.
Place beef steaks in skillet and brown on both sides.
Pour off drippings, if needed.
Season steak with salt, thyme leaves and pepper.
Top with onion and jalapeno pepper.
Cover and continue cooking 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove steak, cut into serving pieces and return to sauce.
Serve over prepared rice, pasta or mashed potatoes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sour creamed baked chicken
directions: Pour
sour cream in bowl; dip chicken in sour cream and let stay
in cream for 20 minutes.
In another bowl, mix bread crumbs, salt,
pepper, paprika, sugar and lemon pepper.
Coat each chicken
piece with bread crumbs and then in sour cream; dip again
in
sour
cream
and again in bread crumbs.	Place chicken on a well greased baking sheet.
Drizzle melted butter over
each piece
of
chicken.
Bake
at 375° for 45 minutes. Turn chicken 2 times while baking.

title: baked cheese and shrimp(east point shrimp)
directions: Butter the bread; cut into 1-inch squares.
Cut cheese into small pieces.
Make layers of bread, shrimp and cheese.
Add 1 tablespoon of shrimp juice.
Mix eggs and milk together and add to the mixture.
Bake at 325° in a buttered dish for 1 hour.

title: seasoned bread crumbs
directions: Dry bread slices at 250° until crisp and golden.
Put in blender on medium speed a few seconds.
Mix in seasonings.
Store covered in dry place.
Makes 1 cup.
Adds just that different gourmet taste to casseroles and salads calling for bread crumb toppings.

title: chuck wagon baked beans
directions: Fry cubed bacon until crisp.
Mix beans, onion, cheese, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, molasses, vinegar and bacon grease. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
In a bowl, stir together dry ingredients. Stir into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet to rack.
Cool. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/8 cup warm water.
Stir 1 1/2 cups warm water, brown sugar and flour in.
Beat until smooth.
Knead until the dough is smooth and elastic.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and stir well. Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Shape into balls or crescents.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: baked bean medley
directions: Combine various beans in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Stir in onion, molasses, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 375° or until onion is tender.
Makes 10 servings.

title: refrigerator dessert
directions: Saute coconut in butter; add vanilla wafers.
Press 2/3 of mixture
in 9 x 12-inch pan. Add hot water to gelatin; add sugar and
lemon	juice.	Set
aside
to thicken.
Whip milk. Whip gelatin
slightly
and
combine with whipped milk.	Pour onto crumbs.
Cover with remaining crumbs and set in refrigerator.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Flour and brown pork chops.
Sprinkle with sugar, nutmeg and raisins.
Add orange juice; cover the pan and heat to boiling. Then at lowered heat, cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Place an orange, cut into sections, on top of the chops during the last 5 minutes of cooking time.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix flour, meal, salt and pepper and dip the slices into this mixture, coating both sides generously.
Fry each slice until golden brown.
Place on paper towel to drain.
Ripe or nearly ripe tomatoes may be fried in the same way, but being juicier, may require more flour in the coating mix.
Bacon grease is the tastiest way to fry them.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place oleo in pan.
Press in vanilla wafers.
Chill.
Mix until creamy the eggs, sugar and butter and chill.
Add strawberries to mixture and pour in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: jessica's quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Lightly coat baking sheet with cooking spray.
Place 1 flour tortilla on baking sheet.
Spoon cheeses over tortilla.
Place another tortilla on top.
Bake 1 minute and turn tortilla over and cook another minute or until cheese is melted.
Cut quesadilla in quarters and serve with sour cream and salsa.
Serves 2.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Flour pork and brown in frying pan with a tablespoon of oil. Mix together the other ingredients.
Place pork chops in large casserole; pour soup mixture over the chops.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sour cream double cornbread
directions: In a very large bowl, mix sugar, salt and yeast.
Add warm water, sourdough mixture and oil.
Add 1/2 of the flour.
Add remaining flour, a little at a time, until you can knead the dough without it sticking.
Place dough in large greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled, punch down and shape into loaves (2 or 3) and let rise again until doubled in size.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread according to package directions; cool. Crumble into large bowl.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, tomato and beans; mix well.
Mix sour cream and Miracle Whip in a small bowl; add to corn bread mixture.
Mix well; chill in refrigerator.

title: hello dollie cookies
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake in 350° oven until brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut immediately upon removal from oven.
Let sit for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Mix buttermilk with dissolved yeast; add to flour mixture.
Cover bowl and refrigerate several hours or up to 3 days.
Take out desired amount of dough.
Roll out on lightly floured board to 3/8-inch thickness.
With biscuit cutter, cut out biscuits.
Dip each in melted butter and place in a pan.
Let rise in a warm place about 30 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: 50 to 60 large or 80 small biscuits.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding pecan meats last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: seaside chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add juice and remaining ingredients, except fish.
Bring to a boil; stir to separate beans.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add fish and cook 10 minutes more or until fish is done.
Makes about 6 cups (4 servings).

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: *May use one slice of bread, with crusts removed, and broken into small pieces.

title: poor richard's bloody mary
directions: Combine ingredients in large shaker or jar and shake well. Use separately as a breakfast drink or use with vodka and ice.

title: tiny meatballs
directions: Mix meat, bread, egg and garlic salt together.
Form into 1-inch balls and brown.

title: dodie's fruit cake(no bake)
directions: Melt in double boiler the marshmallows, oleo and juice of maraschino cherries.
In large pan mix dry ingredients.
Pour mixture from double boiler over dry ingredients (slowly).
Mix well.
Pack in tube pan well.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Slice thin and serve.

title: hurry-up chicken
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of casserole dish, laying first one way, then the other.
Pour 1/2 bottle of Italian dressing over chicken.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup bread crumbs over top.
Cover and place in microwave.
Cook 10 minutes.
Check for doneness.
Do 1 minute intervals until done.

title: hot garlic dill pickles
directions: Sterilize 6 quart jars and lids.
Make solution of vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Put 1 each of garlic, pepper, onion and 1 teaspoon dill seed in each jar.
Pack cucumbers in jars.
Pour boiling liquid in jars and cap.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices together. Toss a little nuts and fruits into flour mixture and beat sugar and oil; mix at low speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add pumpkin to flour mixture and water.
Beat well until thoroughly mixed.
Put in a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°:
Lightly spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Place spaghetti in prepared pie plate. Top with Velveeta Italiana pasteurized cheese spread and spaghetti sauce.
Bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with fresh parsley, if desired.
Cut into wedges. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hobo supper
directions: On a square of aluminum foil, place the hamburger or ground beef.
Place a slice of onion, potato, carrot and celery on top. Dot vegetables with butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Wrap foil drug store style.
Repeat until hamburger is all used.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 325 degrees for 45-55 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions with butter and a little salt and pepper. After squash has cooked down, add salt, pepper and remaining ingredients. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: maraschino quick cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir shortening just to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add cherry juice, cherries and milk.
Mix until all flour is dampened.
Then beat vigorously 2 minutes.
Add egg whites; beat vigorously 2 minutes longer.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 2 paper lined 8-inch pans in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with any frosting but best with whipped cream frosting.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix wet ingredients, except berries, in a small bowl.
Add wet to dry ingredients. Stir until moistened.
Lumps should remain.
Fold in berries.

title: favorite (and healthy) muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix yogurt and milk well.
Gently stir in dry ingredients just until moistened.
Blend in chocolate chips.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Combine Bisquick mix, sugar, milk, egg and shortening.
Stir well.
Batter will be lumpy.
Add grated cheese.
Stir and put into muffin tins.
Yield: approximately 1 dozen.

title: chocolate peanut butter parfaits(low-fat)
directions: Add 2 tablespoons milk to peanut butter; stir until well blended.
Stir in whipped topping.
Pour the remaining 2 cups milk into bowl.
Add the pudding mix; beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Spoon half the pudding mixture into 6 parfait glasses. Cover with whipped topping mixture.
Top with remaining pudding. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: irish dish
directions: Put ham, onions and a little vegetable oil in a skillet and let simmer until done.
Put water on this mixture and let come to a boil.
Put potatoes into this mixture and cook until done.
Stir once in a while.
Use enough ingredients to make enough for your family.

title: kraut stuffed pork chops
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Add chops.
Cook until browned on both sides.
Remove and set aside, reserving drippings.
Slice 4 rings from green peppers and set aside.
Dice remaining peppers.
Add remaining butter or margarine to drippings in skillet.
Add diced pepper and onion.
Cook over medium heat until crisp and tender.
Add carrots.
Cook 1 minute. Stir in sauerkraut, sugar, salt, pepper and thyme.
Mix until well blended.
Preheat oven to 350°.
With a sharp knife, cut each chop horizontally from fat side to bone.
Stuff kraut in pocket.
Cook until done.

title: pottsfield pickles
directions: Chop tomatoes and grind the rest of the ingredients.
Let stand overnite, then drain; add 3 pints vinegar, 2 pounds of sugar, 2 tablespoons mixed spices tied in a bag, 1/2 cup mustard seed.
Cook 2 hours then jar.

title: colonial apple pie
directions: Line 9-inch pan with 1/2 of pastry or use any prepared crust. Arrange apples in unbaked shell.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with remaining crust and flute and seal edges.
Slash several holes in top for air to come out.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until crust is golden brown and apples are tender.

title: trifle dish dessert
directions: Crumble cake.
Put a layer of cake on bottom of dish.
Add pudding, fruits (mixed together) and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers until all are used.
Good dessert for a group.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: simple quick rolls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and let rise for 2 hours. Shape into balls and place in muffin pan.
Let rise in pan for 1 hour.
Bake in oven at 350°, about 35 to 40 minutes, or until brown.

title: fresh water fish
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and pepper into a smooth paste. Add egg.
In a heavy iron skillet, heat enough fat to half fill skillet.
Fat is at proper temperature when a drop of batter forms a ball.
Dip fish in batter and drop in fat.
Turn to even cooking and cook 7 to 8 minutes, until batter coating is golden brown. Remove and put in paper lined pan in warm oven.
Serve with hush puppies.

title: ruby doyle's punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice and Kool-Aid, using 3/4 cup or more sugar to taste; refrigerate.
Minutes before serving, slice ice cream in half; pour ginger ale into mixture that was refrigerated and put half of the ice cream into punch bowl.
Using ladle, pour mixture of punch over ice cream a few times.

title: mama's pecan pie(pecans are all the way through)
directions: Boil sugar and water until it "threads" (soft ball on candy thermometer).
Pour over pecans.
Melt together the flour and margarine.
Add egg yolks.
Pour sugar and water syrup over this. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in unbaked crust at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: mom's baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt and sugar and stir until sugar dissolves.
Slowly add milk to egg mixture.
Add nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pudding dish or cups.
Place dish in pan of hot water in a moderate oven and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°, until custard is firm in center.
Test with knife; if knife comes out clean, custard is done.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Put nuts and egg white into a bowl.
Stir until nuts are coated.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add nuts.
Stir until coated.
Spread on baking sheet.
Bake in a slow 300° oven until crisp and dried, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In baked pie shell, slice banana into shell.
Prepare pie filling mix as directed on box, using 2 1/2 cups cold milk.
Fold in 1/2 cup whipped cream and pour over bananas in pie shell. Chill at least 3 hours.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with banana slices and mint if desired.

title: egg rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix with remaining ingredients to make a soft dough.
Let rise until double in bulk. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll on floured board; cut into rolls. Fold over a thin slice of butter.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and drain grease.
In a separate bowl, mix soup; add milk for consistency.
Mix all ingredients together with taco seasoning mix.

title: noodles and ham
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan. Blend flour into melted butter to form paste. Add cream, stirring constantly, until smooth, thick sauce forms.
Add cheese.
Stir sauce until cheese melts.
Add horseradish, peas, ham and noodles. Blend well.
Pour mixture into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Put wafers in cupcake liners in muffin tin.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Beat for 5 minutes with a beater.
Spoon 2 tablespoons in each cupcake liner.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Makes about 18.

title: crunchies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and place in greased brownie-size pan.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix on medium speed until well blended.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and 16 ounce bag butterscotch bits.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, pineapple, marshmallows and cherries. Pour into ice tray.
Put in freezer unit.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Begin 30 minutes ahead.
In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook salt pork until lightly browned; add onions and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add enough water to clam liquid to make 2 cups.
Stir flour into onion mixture until blended.
Gradually stir in clam-liquid mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.

Stir in potatoes, salt, celery salt and pepper; cover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes. Chop clams; add clams, milk and butter to pan; cover and cook until heated through, about 5 minutes, stirring.
Garnish with parsley. Makes 4 servings or 10 cups.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix together Parmesan cheese, oregano, basil, pepper and garlic powder; set aside.
Dip the chicken in the Italian dressing and then in the cheese mixture.
Place in a lightly greased (with margarine), shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tender.

title: cinnamon carrots
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, stir together cornstarch, tomato juice, brown sugar and cinnamon until smooth.
Over medium heat, cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Add carrots.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 servings.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cook time:
15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together cake mix (minus 1 cup), 1 stick oleo and egg and pat dough in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix pumpkin, eggs, milk, brown sugar and cinnamon, then pour over dough.
To 1 cup reserved cake mix, add 1/4 cup oleo and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Sprinkle on top of cake. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup of pecans.
Mix with hands until
all
one color.
Form ball and roll in nuts. Chill.

title: microwave cookie crumble
directions: Thaw the whipped topping.
Open can of pie filling.
Pour into 9-inch microwavable dish.
Place cookies in a plastic bag.
Close bag and break up cookies and sprinkle over the filling.
Microwave on High for one minute.
Spoon onto plates and top with the whipped topping or serve over ice cream.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream margarine, pumpkin, eggs, vanilla, raisins and nuts. Sift flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Combine dry ingredients to creamed mixture and drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly less than the package says.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, soup, egg and cheese.
Add broccoli.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Mix butter and stuffing.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fried macaroni and swiss cheese
directions: Any leftovers, reheat in microwave.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and margarine 8 minutes.
Add chips and marshmallow cream; beat well.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish and cut into squares.
Freeze if desired.

title: kraut
directions: Chop cabbage until fine.
Pack loosely in quart jars.
Add 2 teaspoons of pickling salt and 1 teaspoon of vinegar to each jar. Fill with cold water and put a two piece lid on each jar.
Set in a cool dark place in a cardboard box (or on papers) as liquid will ooze out during fermentation process.
Will be ready to eat in 3 to 4 weeks.

title: pork chops hawaiian
directions: Sprinkle chops
with
salt and pepper.
Coat with flour and brown on one side in hot shortening.
Mix pineapple, sugar and cinnamon.
Turn
chops
and
cover with pineapple mixture; reduce heat to
simmer.
Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes until chops are tender.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: lamb with eggplant and rice
directions: Soak cubes of eggplant in salted water for 15 minutes.
Rinse and drain well.
Brown lamb on all sides in hot fat.
Transfer to casserole.
Pan-fry onion until golden.
Add eggplant, seasonings and consomme to casserole.
Brown rice in a dry skillet; add tomatoes with juice to rice.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° until lamb is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza supper sandwich
directions: In a medium skillet, brown the beef until crumbly.
Drain. Mix in onion, tomato paste and steak sauce.
Keep warm.
Place bread on a large cookie sheet.
Spread with margarine.
Toast under broiler until brown.
Spread with meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Broil 4 to 6 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: noodles
directions: Stir sufficient flour into slightly beaten eggs and water to make a stiff dough.
Knead thoroughly.
Divide into two portions and roll out as thin as possible.
Cover with a cloth and leave until partly dry.
Then roll and cut in 1/2-inch strips.
Part of the dough may be cut very fine to be used as topping on the cooked noodles.
Boil noodles in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Brown 1/2 cup finely cut noodles in butter and pour over the cooked noodles before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crust:
Crush cookies and mix with softened butter.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and allow to refrigerate overnight.
This will make salad firm and hold its shape.

title: low-fat snack mix
directions: Combine the liquid mixture with the dry mixture.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave mixture in oven for another hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar in plastic quart size bag.
Shake to mix well.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Drop in bag and coat well. Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Heat butter (or margarine), brown sugar and water in saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes. Pour over biscuits and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and pour over the salad. This is better if it sets overnight.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Cook potatoes, leeks, celery, carrots and onion in enough water to keep from sticking until tender.
Add chicken broth, garlic, Accent, salt, and pepper.

title: sugar beet cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well.
Blend in beets.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix first three ingredients and cover in ice; let set for 3 hours, then drain.
Mix together other ingredients in large pan. Add cucumber mixture and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
