Sift together the dry ingredients and set aside.
Grate the washed carrots on medium grater or use coarse blade of food processor.
(Should measure about 4 cups.)
In large bowl of mixer at high speed, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy, about 4 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until smooth and light.
In measuring cup combine fruit juices and peels.
At low speed beat in flour mixture (in 4ths) along with juice and peels (in 3rds), beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat just until smooth (about 1 minute).
With wooden spoon stir in carrots, nuts and raisins.
Mix well and spread evenly into prepared pan.
Bake 60 minutes in pan and turn out onto cooling rack.
Top with following Cream Cheese Glaze.

title: golden apple cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and allspice together.
Combine oil, sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour mixture and oats; spread in greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: homemade bologna
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into rolls.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: laura's chili
directions: Grill the ribeyes on the grill with liquid smoke.
In the meantime, brown the beef, chicken or turkey in nonstick deep pan. Season the meat with your choice of seasonings.
Add the mushrooms and onion with the raw meat.
After meat is cooked, drain and add soup, stewed tomatoes, pinto beans and beer.
After steaks are cooked, dice and add to chili.
Season to taste with your favorite choice of seasonings.

title: muscadine punch
directions: Chill drinks in freezer until slushy and mix together with muscadine juice.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Put 3 slices of cubed bread in casserole dish.
Add 1 cup chicken and 2 more slices of cubed bread.
Beat eggs, milk, soup and mayonnaise.
Mix well; pour over chicken and bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and dot with butter.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup and almonds.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir asparagus and pimento and spoon on top of chicken mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle on onions around edge and bake 5 minutes more.

title: chicken dorito
directions: Mix soup, water, Ro-Tel tomatoes and onion.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer Doritos, chicken, soup and cheese.
Repeat as necessary.
End with cheese on top of Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned salmon loaf
directions: Spoon into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until the knife comes out clean and top is browned.

title: greens with bacon
directions: Clean greens and cut up 2 days ahead. Make sure you clean greens really well.
Cook bacon in 4 to 5-quart pot until crisp. Drain bacon on paper towel.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Cut onions in bacon fat over medium heat and cook 5 to 6 minutes, stirring, until translucent.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to boil; add bacon and bring to boil.
Add greens, a batch at a time, adding more as they cook down.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until leaves are tender and liquid is reduced by half.
Add crushed red peppers over greens.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg, molasses and sour milk, which has had cup
of bran soaking in it. Add dry ingredients. Bake at 375°
for
20 minutes.
Makes 18 medium-sized muffins.

title: garnell's "no bake chocolate cookies"
directions: Mix together in kettle:
sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo.
Let come to a boil.
Add 1 cup peanut butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool until completely dry.
When tops are dry, turn over.
Store in dry place in cans or plastic containers. Enjoy!!!

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Pound veal cutlets slightly and dust with flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook them quickly on both sides in olive oil and butter.
When brown on both sides, remove to a platter and keep warm.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix everything except sugar.
After everything is mixed good, add sugar and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: heath bark
directions: Lightly spray a cookie sheet.
Line with saltine crackers (single layer).

title: waldorf astoria cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; add alternately along with milk.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts last.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In large pan scald the 4 1/2 cups of milk, set aside.
Combine sugar, salt, eggs and flour; add to scalded milk.
Cook until it boils, stirring to prevent burning.
Add vanilla and canned milk, cool.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Strain into a gallon freezer can and add enough milk to fill can 2/3 full and freeze.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer 1/2 of each ingredient as listed, then repeat.
Garnish with pecans, coconut and cherries.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Stuff
chilies
with
cheese
(careful not to rip sides open). Roll
in
flour and set aside.
In a bowl with the egg beater, mix
whites until they peak.
In a separate bowl, mix egg yolks with flour and gently fold the yolks into the white. With a big spoon, put chilies in egg whites.
Cover chili well and
put
in hot oil.
Cook quickly until golden brown on both sides.
Place on paper towel.
Serve with salsa on top.

title: butterfinger delights
directions: Mix crumbs with margarine; save 1/4 cup.
Put crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press.
Mix pudding with milk.
Let ice cream soften, then mix with pudding.
Pour over crumbs and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crumble Butterfingers and add remainder of crumb mixture.
Sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: poulet champignon "chicken with mushrooms"
directions: Broil chickens with salt, pepper, sage and paprika sprinkled on it until brown.
Mix soup, sherry and mushrooms.
Put chicken in bottom of broiler pan.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes until done.
Serve with rice.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Put butter in baking dish to melt.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Add butter and pour back in baking dish.
Pour fruit of choice over top and bake 1 hour at 325 degrees until brown and bubbly.

title: breakfast tortilla(good for camping for a bunch and at home.)
directions: Put hash brown potatoes in frying pan and brown.
Fry sausage and onion until done.
Mix a little of milk with the eggs and scramble until done.
Put all 3 ingredients (sausage, eggs and hash browns) in a dish and mix.
Warm the tortillas in oven or microwave.
Put the 3 jars of salsa on table with sour cream, cheese and tortillas.
Put the egg mixture on first, then cheese and salsa.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper; simmer with onion, garlic, soup and sour cream.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer meat mix, then layer of sliced frozen spinach until gone.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese, shaved.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Cover with water and add seasoning.
Let simmer until water is gone.
Add meat on top of lettuce.
Add diced tomatoes and cheese.
Put sauce on top of meat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cocktail meatballs or kielbasa
directions: Melt together chili sauce and cranberry sauce.
Add brown sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over either meatballs, sliced kielbasa or cocktail franks.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix and bake in greased loaf pan for approximately 50 minutes at 350°.

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Butter foil. Layer with crackers.

title: spinach with rice
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in olive oil until translucent.
Add spinach.
Mix tomato paste with water and add along with rice. Cover.
Simmer until rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef and sausage.
Add chopped onion.
Beat eggs in dish. Add to mixture.
Then mix crackers or bread crumbs to stiffen. Add salt and pepper.
Make into a loaf.
Put in loaf pan, greased. Then make small dents in the middle.
Pour ketchup into them. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake in medium oven (350°) until firm (about 1 hour).
Serve plain or with cream.

title: low calorie fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture into bowl.
Top with half of fruit.
Pour remaining mixture over fruit.
Next, top with remaining fruit.
Chill before serving.
(I use strawberries, grapes, bananas and kiwi, but any combination may be used.)

title: italian stuffed swiss chard
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, cut off tough stems of Swiss chard. Remove 8 large leaves; trim ribs of leaves very thin. Coarsely chop remaining Swiss chard to measure about 4 cups loosely packed.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot olive or salad oil, cook onion until it begins to brown, about 10 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together; finish filling freezer with milk and freeze.

title: cordon bleu
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook pepper, onion, celery, mushrooms and pimentos in tomatoes until tender.
Make 4 cups creamed sauce made with chicken broth and canned milk to which 1 pound of grated American cheese has been added.
Add cooked vegetable mixture.
Add chicken.
Add red pepper, Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.
Cook about 1 1/2 pounds of spaghetti and mix in with chicken mixture.
Add more or less spaghetti to your own taste.
Freezes well and may be halved.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda together in bowl.
Add oil and eggs; mix well.
Stir in strawberries and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pans for several minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Prepare frozen broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Blend together soup and flour.
Add sour cream, carrot, onion, salt and pepper; stir in broccoli.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Combine stuffing mix and melted oleo.
Sprinkle around edge of baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot through.
Makes 6 servings.
Can easily be doubled.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan with an extra amount of softened butter, then lightly flour.
Set aside.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa and butter; add milk for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on cake pan. Let harden.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time mixing well after adding each one.
Add flour.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Tastes great with fresh strawberries and vanilla ice cream.

title: dairy potato bake
directions: Mix all together except corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flakes and butter.
Sprinkle with the paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy twice baked potatoes
directions: Prepare 8 servings of instant mashed potatoes.
Into that beat an 8 ounce package of cream cheese.
Add egg and dry onions to potato mixture.
Place in ungreased casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan or Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dorgie's cornbread casserole
directions: Mix cornbread according to package directions.
Add corn; set aside.
In skillet, brown meat and onion.
Add salt, pepper, taco mix and jalapeno pepper.
Put 1/2 cornbread mixture in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Add meat mixture, then layer of cheese. Top with remaining cornbread mixture and grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until top is brown.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in butter (do not brown).
Add chicken broth and broccoli.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to a boil and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix the above ingredients together and place into a pie shell. Bake at 425° until set.
Use knife to test.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Blend together.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in by hands nuts, dates and cherries.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours or may be chilled overnight. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers in cold water, then put in ice water with plenty of ice and let stand for 24 hours.
Drain and pack into jars, as tight as possible.
To each quart jar, add alum, dill weed, red peppers and garlic.
Mix white vinegar, 3 quarts water and canning salt; bring to boil and pour over cucumbers.
Seal.
Let set for 5 weeks.

title: baby apricot salad
directions: Partially freeze cream cheese for easier cutting.
Combine Jell-O and pineapple with juice in a saucepan and heat to simmering.
Add sugar and apricots and remove from heat.
Cool a little before adding cream cheese which has been cut in small squares.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in topping.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch dish and sprinkle with pecans.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish for 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange-apple-cranberry relish
directions: Boil (low to medium) together until cranberries burst, then simmer 5 minutes.

title: mack's cabbage mix (casserole)
directions: Cover bottom
of large skillet with oil; add first four ingredients and
fry.
Stir
in mushrooms and cook until done. Add bouillon,
water and cabbage and cook until done.
Vegetables will be soft.

title: angel squares
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar (reserve 2 tablespoons) and set aside.
Mix cake mix, butter and nuts.
Pat cake mixture into 11 x 15-inch greased pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top of cake mixture and spread evenly.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350° (until golden brown).
Sprinkle 2 reserved tablespoons on top when done.
We call them Angel Squares because they are so heavenly.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add eggs; cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows; mix well.

title: tidbits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in large pan (broiler pan will do nicely) for 45 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Oven temperature should be 250°.

title: peanut butter fudge(5 pounds)
directions: Into large, heavy pan place sugar, butter and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until ingredients melt.
Continue cooking to soft ball stage (235°).
Remove from heat; quickly stir in peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour into 2 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) greased pans.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter and blend in sugar, eggs and the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into 9-inch pie shell and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate baskets with berry cream
directions: Invert six 6-ounce custard cups; cover each with a paper baking cup, then with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Make sure paper cup stays in place.
Place inverted cups on baking sheet.
Coat with cooking spray.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Let tortillas stand at room temperature while preparing filling.

title: simple chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in the Eagle Brand milk. Add nuts and flavoring. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and then pumpkin.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, a few inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: slaw
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain French beans and carrots; put in large bowl.
Mix well vinegar,
sugar,
oil, salt, red pepper and black pepper. Pour mixture
over
beans and carrots. Cover with onion rings; weigh down.
Cover and leave out overnight.

title: sauce for peppers, tomatoes or cabbage
directions: Place all
ingredients in saucepan and simmer for about 5 minutes; pour around the stuffed vegetables.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Crumble half cake in punch bowl. Add half of pudding mix.
Spread half pie filling around outer edges of punch bowl.
Add half pineapple on the inside of pie filling.
Cover with half cool whip.
Repeat recipe with remaining half of ingredients and enjoy!!

title: mary todd lincoln's election cake
directions: Soak the currants or raisins in 1/2 cup brandy overnight in a tightly closed jar.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar to the scalded milk; cool.
Dissolve the yeast cake in 1/4 cup water; add to milk.
Add 1 cup flour; beat until well blended.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: easy frying pan bread
directions: Put flour and salt in bowl, rub in butter, add water.
Keep mixing until a pliable dough is formed.
Lightly oil bowl, add dough, cover with damp cloth, rest for 1/2 hr.

title: mexican mix-up
directions: Brown beef, onion, green pepper and add spices.
Add the gravy, beans and macaroni.
Pour mixture into baking dish and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Stir, then top with cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put in bottom of casserole.
Place bread crumbs over sausage.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Pour over sausage.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix but do not boil the oil, garlic, dill and dressing. Everything should dissolve. Add crackers and mix well. Cool on cookie sheet. Store in airtight container.

title: albondigas soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil and saute onion and garlic until golden brown. Add tomato sauce, water and bouillon cubes and heat to boiling.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Beat well. Add chili sauce, clams and horseradish.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Add flour, meal, lemon juice and rind.
Pour mixture in pie shells. Bake at 350° until done.
This makes 2 pies.

title: magic bisquick custard pie
directions: Blend for 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop - potato casserole
directions: Brown the pork chops over medium heat.
Arrange in a 2-quart casserole the sliced potatoes, then salt and pepper to taste. Slice the onion into very thin slices; arrange on top of potatoes. Pour over all 1/2 of the soup.
Repeat the procedure.
Place browned chops on top.
Cover and bake for about 1 hour in a 350° oven or until tender all the way through.

title: santa fe stew
directions: Brown meat, then drain off excess fat.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
When you put in jar of salsa, fill empty jar about 1/2 full of water.
Add flour, then shake until smooth.
Put in crock-pot and cook at 350° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: pepparkakar christmas cookies(pepper-cogger)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add butter gradually to sugar, creaming well.
Add molasses.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Add chopped almonds.
Dough will be very stiff.
Shape into a roll; chill and slice or roll out on a very lightly floured board and cut out.
Use a spatula to lift onto cookie sheet.
These freeze real good.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to boil to dissolve.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Mix in egg yolks. Stir in cream.
Cook, uncovered, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Spread small amount on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Make a layer of wafers, top with a layer of sliced bananas.
Pour about 1/3 of custard over bananas.
Continue to make layers ending with custard on top.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased bread pan or pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 1 regular size loaf or 2 extra small loaves.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Saute meat, celery and onion.
Add rest of ingredients and mix in large casserole dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles over last 1/2 hour.

title: pepped up potato salad
directions: Soak mustard and celery in vinegar overnight.
Combine seed mixture with salt and onions.
Add potatoes and mix.
Add mayo and chopped eggs; toss to mix.
Chill.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add shortening and mix well.
Blend in sugar. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla flavoring. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 3 layers.

title: candied yams
directions: Drain water off yams; drain juice from pineapple.
Blend pineapple juice with brown sugar until smooth.
Mix pineapple, blended sugar and marshmallows with yams.
Add cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until top is crusted.

title: nutritions delicious lunchbox cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water together until about 5 tablespoons liquid remains. Drain and cool liquid. Preheat oven to 375°. Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together thoroughly.

Stir in the cool raisin liquid and vanilla. Stir dry ingredients together and stir in oatmeal and cooked raisins. Drop by spoon about 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: ellie's grandma's zucchini cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in zucchini.
Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add almonds and chocolate chips.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool.
Sift powdered sugar over top.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: swiss steak
directions: Remove excess fat from steak.
Put meat on well floured cutting board.
Score meat by cutting diamond shaped on top of meat on both sides.
Cover steak with flour and brown sugar. Using meat hammer (or edge of plate), beat flour into meat, turning to each side until meat and brown sugar have been taken up.
Melt excess fat in skillet and brown onions.
Remove onions and brown steak on both sides.
Place onions on top of steak.
Add tomatoes and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours more in 350° oven or electric skillet.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Blend eggs and milk.
Mix salt, brown sugar and cornstarch. Add egg and milk mixture to this dry mixture.
Add butter and cook over low heat until smooth and thick.
Stir constantly.
Cool and add vanilla.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend in buttermilk, jam and raisins.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown meat; add onion and put all other ingredients in pan. Put spices in bag (cotton/cheesecloth tied at top) and place with other ingredients in pan.
Simmer for about 1 hour.
Serves about 25.

title: chicken cheese bake
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish, which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese; top with tomato.
Combine with stuffing; sprinkle over tomato.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: sun bundt cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and butter extract.
Mix sugar, pecans and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Stir well and add to batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: salmon cheese casserole
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Pour into lightly greased crock-pot. Cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours.

title: ginger shrimp toast
directions: Preheat broiler.
Using a 1 1/2 to 2 -inch cookie cutter, cut bread slices into rounds.
Toast on one side only.
Cream butter and salt.
Stir in minced shrimp, garlic, parsley and ginger. Blend well.
Spread mixture on untoasted side of bread rounds. Place on cookie sheet and broil until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.
Yields 50 to 60 rounds.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press evenly onto bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on top of crust.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until smooth. Gradually beat in milk.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Spread evenly over bananas.
Spoon pineapple over pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep up to a week in the refrigerator.

title: creamy filling or frosting
directions: Beat together butter, shortening and flour.
Then add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Beat 12 more minutes.
Mixture will be smooth and creamy.

title: apricot jello mold
directions: Put Jell-O, pineapple and sugar into a small saucepan.
Cook slowly on the stove, on low heat, for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Pineapple juice will make its own liquid.)
Remove from the heat.
Add the cream cheese and nuts to the mixture.
Fold in the entire container of prepared Dream Whip.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add the remaining ingredients. Cover the pan and cook for 30 minutes.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Trim the fat from the chops.
Brown them in a large pan. Meanwhile, place the onion slices on the bottom of a large shallow baking dish.
Place the pork chops on top of the onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine the chicken bouillon cube with the mustard and the water. Drizzle over the chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tangy barbecue turkey tenderloins
directions: The Michigan Pork Producers Association offers these suggestions for preparing ribs.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cheez Whiz; pour in a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread Cheez Whiz evenly over top.
Bake 15 minutes longer until hot and bubbly in center.

title: spreading cheese
directions: Let milk sour until it is very thick.
Heat until it is too hot to hold your hand in, but hot boiling.
Drain through a coarse cloth bag, putting only half of the milk through at a time so as to be able to squeeze out all water possible.
It is is too hot, hold bag under running water a minute to cool.
Put in a bowl and crumble.
This makes 4 cups or a little more of crumbs.
Let set at room temperature for 2 to 3 days or longer if a stronger taste is desired.

title: super bean salad
directions: Place drained beans in a large bowl and toss gently.
Combine jelly, vinegar, cornstarch and salt in a small pan and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over beans and toss to coat the vegetables.
Cool.
Toss in celery and onions.
Serve chilled.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Cook onions and bacon together.
Mix all ingredients together. May add juice from beans if you need more liquid.
Bake in 2-quart dish, uncovered, at 350°
for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Broil chicken breasts until tender.
Tear and cut into bite-size pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips, if desired.

title: goulash
directions: In a large pot, brown the meat on all sides in the oil.
Do not drain.
Add ketchup and a cup or 2 of water.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours; adding water if mixture becomes too thick.
Stir occasionally.
Sauce should resemble spaghetti sauce in thickness. In a separate pot, cook noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Serve sauce over noodles and serve.

title: chinese chicken with vegetables
directions: Brown chicken in wok coated with Pam.
Add vegetables and cook for 1 minute.
Dissolve chicken soup supplement in water.
Pour over chicken and add seasonings.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes. Remove cover and cook until liquid thickens.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine in a roaster pan.
Stir in seasonings. Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels.
Stir to coat.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: shrimp
directions: Melt butter and mix ingredients, except shrimp.
Pour over shrimp.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: layered cabbage salad
directions: Put all the cauliflower in the bottom of a large bowl.
Top with 1/3 of the cabbage.
In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, pepper and salt.
Spread half of this dressing on top of cabbage.
Layer on another 1/3 of the cabbage.
Top with half the bacon and half the cheese.

title: long island ice tea
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Add additional Coke before serving.
Makes 10 gallons.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss together the lettuce, tomato and onion. Add Doritos, cheese and ground beef in that order. Pour dressing on top and toss.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together plus salt and pepper to taste. Add bacon and cashews just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: pasta with tomatoes
directions: Cook garlic in oil until golden.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, red pepper and sugar.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat to low. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook pasta and drain.
Stir pasta into tomato mixture; top with Parmesan cheese.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 325° or 350° until brown.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain and chop up peaches.
Whip together cream cheese, Cool Whip and dry jello.
Add cottage cheese and peaches to mixture. Chill for four hours and serve.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet over medium heat until crisp. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic to reserved drippings.
Cook over medium heat until tender and most of mushroom liquid has evaporated, about 6 to 8 minutes.

title: selwyn's chili
directions: *Any brand will do, but try to get seasonings that have 3 packets:
1 seasoning, 1 masa flour and 1 hot chili spice.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Put all the ingredients in one bowl and stir until everything is mixed well.
Pour in a well greased 9 x 15-inch dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute
ground
meat
and
chopped onion.
Do not brown. Add garlic
powder, oregano, parsley flakes, salt and pepper. Add to water,
soup,
sauce and tomato paste in crock-pot and let simmer 3
hours.
Cook lasagna as directed on package and drain.
Use
a large baking dish and grease lightly with oleo. Layer
lasagna, sauce
and
Mozzarella
and
Ricotta cheeses. Repeat layers
and top
with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave cracker jacks
directions: Grease a grocery bag with Pam.
In a 2-quart or larger glass dish, place brown sugar, Karo syrup, margarine and salt.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave on High 4 minutes and be sure that the mixture is boiling at least 2 minutes.
Stir into syrup mixture the 1/2 teaspoon soda.
If using peanuts, add to the syrup and stir in now.
Pour over popcorn.
In bag, shake 2 minutes. Fold over top of bag.
Shake 2 minutes.
Fold over top of bag. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes longer.
Shake again.
Pour into a large greased pan to cool.

title: becky's strawberry crunch
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo, and sugar together for crust.
Bake 10 minutes on 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, and Cool Whip and pour on crust.
Mix Jell-O according to directions. Add strawberries.
Pour on top of cream mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and cool. Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Add tomatoes last so they don't come apart.
Finish with enough salt, pepper and mayonnaise to suit your family.
Chill.
Enjoy!

title: errands-to-run chicken
directions: Top chicken with undiluted soup and bake at 375° for 70 minutes.
You can add small chunks of potatoes to the chicken and top them also.
Ignore this and run your errands while this is baking!
You can use chicken noodle soup also.
Makes for a crunchy topping!
Serves 6.

title: rosamarina dessert
directions: Cook rosamarina according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Drain juices from pineapple, orange and cherries.
Save juices.
Cook juice with flour, salt, eggs and sugar.
Boil (won't be thick).
Mix with rosamarina while liquid is hot.
Refrigerate overnight.
Fold in fruit and Cool Whip and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Place tortilla shells on bottom of a greased 9 X 13 pan until covered.
Brown hamburger, drain and add taco seasoning as package directs.
Add beans to burger mix, and mix well.
Spread beans/meat mixture over tortillas.	Spread with sour cream. Sprinkle on a layer of each:
lettuce, tomatoes, onions & cheese. Top with another layer of shells.
Mix together gravy & enchilada sauce and pour over top of shells.	Sprinkle on more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.	Let stand before serving.
